46
00:02:18.417 --> 00:02:22.185
♪ IT GOES ON
AND ON AND ON ♪

47
00:02:22.187 --> 00:02:27.190
♪ STRANGERS WAITING ♪

48
00:02:27.226 --> 00:02:28.258
♪ WALKING DOWN
THE BOULEVARD... ♪


49
00:02:28.393 --> 00:02:30.127
[SCOFFS]

50
00:02:30.262 --> 00:02:32.729
AREN'T YOU WORRIED
ABOUT HARVARD GIRLS?


51
00:02:32.731 --> 00:02:33.863
THEY SEEM
SO ACCOMPLISHED.


52
00:02:33.899 --> 00:02:34.931
I SAW THIS SHOW ONCE,

53
00:02:34.967 --> 00:02:37.200
SOME HARVARD GIRL
RAN A WHOLE COUNTRY.


54
00:02:38.971 --> 00:02:40.137
NO, I'M NOT
REALLY WORRIED


55
00:02:40.272 --> 00:02:41.204
ABOUT HARVARD GIRLS.

56
00:02:41.339 --> 00:02:43.874
I MEAN, JOHN AND I
ARE IN LOVE.


57
00:02:44.009 --> 00:02:45.275
ARE YOU GOING TO WEAR
THAT STUPID CROWN TO BED?


58
00:02:45.277 --> 00:02:47.144
WE GET IT, YOU RULE.

59
00:02:47.146 --> 00:02:49.479
LITTLE JEALOUS,
MICHELLE?


60
00:02:49.515 --> 00:02:50.680
OF WHAT,

61
00:02:50.716 --> 00:02:52.015
SOME DUMB FOOTBALL PLAYER?

62
00:02:52.150 --> 00:02:53.950
NO. I'VE GOT NICK.

63
00:02:55.888 --> 00:02:57.020
NICK'S A GREAT GUY.

64
00:02:57.022 --> 00:02:58.020
AND HE'S MINE NOW.

65
00:02:58.057 --> 00:02:59.623
HE DOESN'T LOVE YOU ANYMORE.

66
00:02:59.758 --> 00:03:02.225
OKAY, MICHELLE,
I KNOW.


67
00:03:02.227 --> 00:03:04.094
NO, YOU DON'T.

68
00:03:04.163 --> 00:03:05.495
YOU DON'T KNOW ANYTHING.

69
00:03:05.531 --> 00:03:06.763
HARVARD GIRLS
ARE SMART AND BEAUTIFUL.


70
00:03:06.765 --> 00:03:09.499
THEY DON'T WORK
AT MARTI'S DINER.


71
00:03:09.634 --> 00:03:11.568
KATHY'S GOT A MUSIC
SCHOLARSHIP TO STATE.


72
00:03:11.570 --> 00:03:13.570
SO WHAT?

73
00:03:13.639 --> 00:03:15.104
YOUR LIFE JUST
PEAKED AT PROM QUEEN,


74
00:03:15.140 --> 00:03:16.573
AND JOHN'S IS JUST BEGINNING.

75
00:03:16.708 --> 00:03:18.441
HE'S GOING TO GO AWAY
AND FORGET ALL ABOUT YOU.


76
00:03:18.477 --> 00:03:19.576
A YEAR FROM NOW,

77
00:03:19.645 --> 00:03:20.577
YOU ARE GOING TO
BE SO EMBARRASSED


78
00:03:20.712 --> 00:03:21.912
BECAUSE HE'LL BE GONE,

79
00:03:22.047 --> 00:03:23.446
AND ALL YOU'LL HAVE
IS THAT STUPID CROWN.


80
00:03:23.515 --> 00:03:25.048
YOU NEED TO SHUT UP,
MICHELLE.


81
00:03:25.117 --> 00:03:27.684
ONE YEAR, AND YOU'RE
GOING TO BE ALL ALONE.


82
00:03:31.857 --> 00:03:33.456
SHE'S JUST UPSET.

83
00:03:33.459 --> 00:03:34.458
SHE KNOWS
SHE ONLY GOT NICK


84
00:03:34.593 --> 00:03:36.460
ON THE REBOUND.

85
00:03:38.397 --> 00:03:40.230
YEAH.

86
00:03:45.270 --> 00:03:46.269
MR. BAUER SAID I DON'T
HAVE TO BE AT WORK


87
00:03:46.338 --> 00:03:47.270
TILL 10:00 TOMORROW,

88
00:03:47.405 --> 00:03:48.738
SO WE CAN STAY OUT
LATER THAN I THOUGHT.


89
00:03:48.774 --> 00:03:50.140
COOL.

90
00:03:50.142 --> 00:03:52.943
HOW COME YOU TOOK
YOUR CROWN OFF?


91
00:03:52.945 --> 00:03:54.076
DIDN'T REALLY FIT.

92
00:03:54.113 --> 00:03:55.144
I LIKED IT.

93
00:03:55.180 --> 00:03:56.546
MADE YOU LOOK
OFFICIAL.


94
00:03:56.615 --> 00:03:57.747
A REAL QUEEN.

95
00:03:57.816 --> 00:03:59.149
OH, YEAH, LIKE
I RUN A COUNTRY?


96
00:03:59.284 --> 00:04:00.951
YEAH.

97
00:04:00.953 --> 00:04:02.218
[CHUCKLES]

98
00:04:02.254 --> 00:04:04.688
ARE YOU HAVING FUN?

99
00:04:04.690 --> 00:04:07.691
I'M WITH YOU,
AREN'T I?


100
00:04:11.997 --> 00:04:16.166
I TALKED TO MAX SEAVER
AT THE DANCE TODAY.


101
00:04:16.168 --> 00:04:19.502
HE LEAVES FOR BASIC
TRAINING TOMORROW.


102
00:04:19.505 --> 00:04:21.237
YEAH, I KNOW.

103
00:04:21.306 --> 00:04:23.106
CHERYL TOLD ME.

104
00:04:23.108 --> 00:04:26.309
I THINK HE'S
A LITTLE SCARED.


105
00:04:26.311 --> 00:04:29.312
WELL, CHERYL IS TOO.

106
00:04:29.447 --> 00:04:33.049
THEY'VE NEVER
BEEN APART.


107
00:04:33.185 --> 00:04:36.119
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

108
00:04:36.254 --> 00:04:39.189
AT LEAST THEY
STILL HAVE THAT.


109
00:04:39.324 --> 00:04:41.124
HMM?

110
00:04:41.126 --> 00:04:42.425
THE MOON.

111
00:04:44.062 --> 00:04:45.128
I MEAN,

112
00:04:45.197 --> 00:04:47.130
HE'LL BE IN GEORGIA,

113
00:04:47.199 --> 00:04:50.734
AND SHE'LL BE
IN BOISE, BUT...


114
00:04:50.736 --> 00:04:55.338
THEY CAN STILL LOOK
AT THE SAME MOON.


115
00:04:55.374 --> 00:04:58.408
IT'S SOMETHING
THEY CAN SHARE,


116
00:04:58.543 --> 00:05:02.179
TO REMIND THEM
THEY'RE STILL IN LOVE.


117
00:05:06.185 --> 00:05:07.350
I WANT TO GO INSIDE.
I'M COLD.


118
00:05:07.485 --> 00:05:09.619
NO, YOU'RE UPSET.

119
00:05:09.754 --> 00:05:12.823
HEY, LOOK AT ME,
LOOK AT ME.


120
00:05:12.958 --> 00:05:16.492
YOU REMEMBER
WHAT I TOLD YOU?


121
00:05:16.562 --> 00:05:17.961
HEY...

122
00:05:17.963 --> 00:05:20.230
I'M TAKING YOUR PICTURE
WITH ME TO HARVARD,


123
00:05:20.299 --> 00:05:23.700
AND I'M LEAVING MY HEART
HERE WITH YOU.


124
00:05:25.137 --> 00:05:28.505
HAVE I EVER
LIED TO YOU?


125
00:05:28.507 --> 00:05:30.106
NO.

126
00:05:30.108 --> 00:05:32.175
THEN DON'T
DOUBT ME NOW.


127
00:05:32.310 --> 00:05:36.178
DON'T DOUBT US.

128
00:05:36.215 --> 00:05:39.782
YOU AND I
ARE FOREVER, KATH.


129
00:05:39.818 --> 00:05:43.086
THE MOON IS OURS TOO.

130
00:05:52.397 --> 00:05:54.397
I LOVE YOU.

131
00:05:54.466 --> 00:05:56.866
BEFORE EVERYTHING.

132
00:05:56.902 --> 00:06:00.337
FOREVER.

133
00:06:01.573 --> 00:06:04.674
I LOVE YOU, TOO.

134
00:06:04.743 --> 00:06:07.911
SO MUCH.

135
00:06:19.825 --> 00:06:22.158
[♪♪]

136
00:06:37.309 --> 00:06:38.774
JOHN!

137
00:06:38.810 --> 00:06:39.909
JOHN, KATHY'S OUT FRONT.

138
00:06:39.912 --> 00:06:41.745
SHE WANTS TO TALK TO YOU.

139
00:06:43.782 --> 00:06:44.580
AND WE'RE ALL OUT OF RELISH.

140
00:06:44.650 --> 00:06:45.581
COULD YOU PICK SOME UP?

141
00:06:45.617 --> 00:06:47.183
SURE.

142
00:06:47.319 --> 00:06:48.718
HEY, DON'T YOU GET
THAT HAT DIRTY.


143
00:06:48.787 --> 00:06:50.186
I GOT TO RETURN IT
TO THE WORRALLS.


144
00:06:50.255 --> 00:06:51.654
RIGHT, HON.

145
00:06:51.657 --> 00:06:54.123
THERE SHE IS.

146
00:06:54.159 --> 00:06:56.525
MOM GAVE US OUR MARCHING ORDERS.

147
00:06:56.561 --> 00:06:58.995
WE GOT TO RUN TO THE STORE,
PICK UP SOME RELISH.


148
00:06:59.064 --> 00:07:01.431
WHY DIDN'T YOU COME IN?

149
00:07:02.868 --> 00:07:04.667
OH, I GET IT.

150
00:07:04.703 --> 00:07:07.137
RELISH FIRST,
FIREWORKS LATER.


151
00:07:07.139 --> 00:07:08.338
JOHN, WAIT.

152
00:07:10.943 --> 00:07:12.042
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

153
00:07:16.682 --> 00:07:18.014
I'M PREGNANT.

154
00:07:27.392 --> 00:07:28.825
ARE YOU SURE?

155
00:07:31.096 --> 00:07:33.963
YEAH.

156
00:07:34.032 --> 00:07:37.700
I WENT TO THE CLINIC.

157
00:07:37.769 --> 00:07:40.203
I'M EIGHT WEEKS PREGNANT.

158
00:07:54.886 --> 00:07:56.186
LET'S CONSIDER
OUR OPTIONS--


159
00:07:56.321 --> 00:07:59.722
THERE ARE NO OPTIONS.

160
00:07:59.725 --> 00:08:01.758
MY MOM GOES TO CHURCH
EVERY SINGLE DAY.


161
00:08:06.932 --> 00:08:09.933
I'LL SNEAK AWAY.

162
00:08:10.068 --> 00:08:11.234
I'LL GET IT DONE SECRETLY.

163
00:08:13.004 --> 00:08:14.070
NO.

164
00:08:14.106 --> 00:08:16.205
WELL, THEN WHAT, JOHN?

165
00:08:16.241 --> 00:08:19.409
WHAT ARE WE
GOING TO DO?


166
00:08:33.692 --> 00:08:35.825
I'LL GO TO STATE
AND GET A NIGHT JOB.


167
00:08:35.960 --> 00:08:38.461
KATHY CAN WATCH
THE BABY.


168
00:08:43.168 --> 00:08:44.300
IT WAS TOUGH FOR YOU
AND DAD IN THE BEGINNING,


169
00:08:44.302 --> 00:08:46.635
BUT YOU MADE IT WORK.

170
00:08:46.671 --> 00:08:48.204
WE WILL TOO.

171
00:08:49.775 --> 00:08:51.041
LOOK, IT ISN'T THE WAY
I WOULD HAVE PLANNED,


172
00:08:51.176 --> 00:08:53.442
BUT KATH AND I WERE ALWAYS
GOING TO GET MARRIED.


173
00:08:53.478 --> 00:08:54.577
OKAY, NOW,
FOUR YEARS FROM NOW,


174
00:08:54.579 --> 00:08:55.578
WHAT IS THE DIFFERENCE?

175
00:08:55.614 --> 00:08:57.313
THE DIFFERENCE
IS HUGE.


176
00:08:57.449 --> 00:08:58.647
YOU ARE GIVING UP
YOUR WHOLE LIFE


177
00:08:58.683 --> 00:08:59.649
IF YOU STAY HERE.

178
00:08:59.718 --> 00:09:00.850
YOU ARE SETTLING FOR
A SACK LUNCH


179
00:09:00.919 --> 00:09:03.052
WHEN THERE'S A BANQUET WAITING
AT HARVARD.


180
00:09:03.088 --> 00:09:06.055
WHAT DO YOU WANT ME TO DO,

181
00:09:06.124 --> 00:09:07.657
GIVE UP ON MY OWN KID?

182
00:09:07.726 --> 00:09:08.858
YOU TAUGHT ME BETTER THAN THAT.

183
00:09:08.927 --> 00:09:12.128
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND,
YOU'RE TOO YOUNG.


184
00:09:12.164 --> 00:09:14.397
HONEY, YOU THINK YOU
HAVE ALL THE ANSWERS


185
00:09:14.532 --> 00:09:16.332
BECAUSE YOU HAVE NEVER FAILED.

186
00:09:16.401 --> 00:09:18.267
IF YOU STAY HERE IN BOISE,
YOU WILL.


187
00:09:18.303 --> 00:09:19.736
YOU WILL FAIL YOURSELF.

188
00:09:19.871 --> 00:09:21.137
YOU WILL FAIL
EVERY DREAM


189
00:09:21.139 --> 00:09:22.938
YOU'VE WORKED
SO HARD FOR.


190
00:09:22.974 --> 00:09:25.475
HAVE THE BABY,

191
00:09:25.610 --> 00:09:28.044
BUT PLEASE
DO NOT ABANDON YOUR FUTURE.


192
00:09:31.616 --> 00:09:32.749
GO TO HARVARD,

193
00:09:32.751 --> 00:09:34.884
OR IT WILL HAUNT YOU
FOR THE REST OF YOUR LIFE.


194
00:09:43.562 --> 00:09:46.695
I JUST LOVE
THIS DRESS.


195
00:09:46.731 --> 00:09:48.364
[SIGHS]: YEAH.

196
00:09:48.366 --> 00:09:49.966
I MEAN,
IT'S NOT EXACTLY


197
00:09:49.968 --> 00:09:54.036
THE DRESS I ALWAYS
DREAMED OF, BUT...


198
00:09:54.072 --> 00:09:55.705
ARE YOU
ABSOLUTELY SURE


199
00:09:55.707 --> 00:09:57.373
YOU WANT TO DO THIS?

200
00:09:57.509 --> 00:10:00.643
[EXHALING NERVOUSLY]

201
00:10:00.645 --> 00:10:03.179
YEAH.

202
00:10:03.181 --> 00:10:04.446
I LOVE HIM.

203
00:10:04.483 --> 00:10:06.715
YEAH, BUT TO GET MARRIED
SO EARLY,


204
00:10:06.751 --> 00:10:09.452
AND, YOU KNOW,
JUST BECAUSE OF AN ACCIDENT.


205
00:10:11.156 --> 00:10:12.721
IT WAS AN ACCIDENT, RIGHT?

206
00:10:12.757 --> 00:10:15.324
I MEAN, YOU DIDN'T MEAN
TO GET PREGNANT,


207
00:10:15.393 --> 00:10:16.859
DID YOU?

208
00:10:16.895 --> 00:10:18.060
WHAT?

209
00:10:18.096 --> 00:10:20.997
I'M SORRY, IT'S JUST,
YOU KNOW, PEOPLE TALK, AND--


210
00:10:21.132 --> 00:10:23.133
YEAH, AND OBVIOUSLY
YOU LISTENED.


211
00:10:23.234 --> 00:10:25.935
ONLY TO DEFEND YOU,
I SWEAR.


212
00:10:25.971 --> 00:10:27.070
HEY.

213
00:10:27.072 --> 00:10:28.938
WE'RE READY.

214
00:10:28.940 --> 00:10:29.872
I JUST...

215
00:10:29.941 --> 00:10:32.942
I WANT A PICTURE
OF THE BRIDE AND HER MOM.


216
00:10:32.944 --> 00:10:34.677
BETH IS GOING TO
MAKE US AN ALBUM.


217
00:10:34.679 --> 00:10:36.112
IT'S HER WEDDING GIFT.

218
00:10:38.283 --> 00:10:40.550
I KNOW I PUT MY CAMERA IN HERE.

219
00:10:41.753 --> 00:10:44.888
OH, GOD...

220
00:10:45.023 --> 00:10:46.489
MAYBE THIS DAY
ISN'T WORTH REMEMBERING.


221
00:10:46.624 --> 00:10:48.758
OH, HONEY...

222
00:10:48.893 --> 00:10:51.627
YOU HAVE SO MUCH
TO LOOK FORWARD TO.


223
00:10:51.696 --> 00:10:53.696
SO MUCH.

224
00:10:53.732 --> 00:10:55.165
OKAY.

225
00:10:55.300 --> 00:10:58.902
IF ANY PERSON
CAN SHOW JUST CAUSE


226
00:10:59.037 --> 00:11:03.839
WHY THESE TWO SHOULD NOT BE
LAWFULLY JOINED TOGETHER,


227
00:11:03.875 --> 00:11:05.842
LET HIM NOW SPEAK,

228
00:11:05.977 --> 00:11:09.245
OR ELSE HEREAFTER

229
00:11:09.314 --> 00:11:14.851
FOREVER
HOLD HIS PEACE.


230
00:11:14.853 --> 00:11:17.353
[♪♪]

231
00:11:19.891 --> 00:11:20.924
I FOUND IT!

232
00:11:21.059 --> 00:11:22.191
IT WAS IN MY CAR!

233
00:11:22.194 --> 00:11:23.793
I GOT IT!

234
00:11:23.795 --> 00:11:25.795
OKAY, EVERYONE,
GATHER 'ROUND, GATHER 'ROUND.


235
00:11:25.864 --> 00:11:28.197
KATHY AND JOHN IN THE CENTER,
PARENTS ON THE OUTSIDE.


236
00:11:28.266 --> 00:11:30.066
CHRIS, SCOOT IN A LITTLE BIT.

237
00:11:30.135 --> 00:11:32.335
OKAY, A LITTLE CLOSER,
LITTLE CLOSER,


238
00:11:32.404 --> 00:11:33.469
AND SHOW SOME SPIRIT!

239
00:11:33.605 --> 00:11:34.637
COME ON, IT'S A WEDDING!

240
00:11:35.907 --> 00:11:36.872
COME ON, GUYS,
HELP ME OUT.


241
00:11:36.942 --> 00:11:38.942
I JUST RAN
IN HIGH HEELS.


242
00:11:39.077 --> 00:11:40.076
OKAY...

243
00:11:40.145 --> 00:11:41.344
AND, CHEESE!

244
00:11:42.614 --> 00:11:44.480
THAT'S THE IDEA!

245
00:11:52.824 --> 00:11:54.690
OH, I FEEL SO MUCH BETTER

246
00:11:54.726 --> 00:11:57.560
NOW THAT HE RECOMMENDED
A DOCTOR IN BOSTON.


247
00:11:57.629 --> 00:11:59.562
OH, MY GOD,
KATHY BLAIR!


248
00:11:59.631 --> 00:12:02.632
I DON'T
BELIEVE IT.


249
00:12:02.634 --> 00:12:04.433
CONGRATULATIONS, GUYS.

250
00:12:04.469 --> 00:12:06.369
I HEARD ABOUT
THE BIG EVENT.


251
00:12:06.371 --> 00:12:08.170
WOW, FROM PROM QUEEN
TO PREGNANT.


252
00:12:08.206 --> 00:12:10.106
YOU ALWAYS WERE
A TRENDSETTER, KATH.


253
00:12:10.175 --> 00:12:11.107
SO, WHAT'S THE PLAN?

254
00:12:11.242 --> 00:12:13.108
KATHY'S COMING WITH ME
TO HARVARD.


255
00:12:13.144 --> 00:12:14.711
REALLY?

256
00:12:14.846 --> 00:12:15.912
WE GOT MARRIED
STUDENT HOUSING,


257
00:12:16.047 --> 00:12:17.980
AND I HAVE A PART-TIME JOB
AT THE HARVARD BOOK STORE


258
00:12:17.983 --> 00:12:19.181
WHILE KATH'LL BE BUSY
WITH THE BABY.


259
00:12:19.251 --> 00:12:20.316
WELL, WE'LL
MISS YOU HERE.


260
00:12:20.352 --> 00:12:22.185
HARVARD
-BOUND, WOW.

261
00:12:22.320 --> 00:12:24.053
I, UH, I SURE
OWE YOU AN APOLOGY.


262
00:12:24.188 --> 00:12:25.921
PROM NIGHT
I WAS ALL OVER YOU


263
00:12:25.957 --> 00:12:26.856
FOR BEING SO DIM,

264
00:12:26.991 --> 00:12:28.391
BUT, BOY, WAS I WRONG.

265
00:12:28.460 --> 00:12:30.592
YOU KNOW EXACTLY
WHAT YOU'RE DOING.


266
00:12:30.629 --> 00:12:31.794
[NICK]: WE'RE GOING
TO MISS THE PREVIEWS.


267
00:12:31.929 --> 00:12:32.929
GOOD LUCK, GUYS.

268
00:12:32.931 --> 00:12:35.064
BYE!

269
00:12:37.002 --> 00:12:39.401
WHAT WAS THAT?

270
00:12:39.437 --> 00:12:40.803
[SCOFFS]:
SHE'S JUST UPSET


271
00:12:40.805 --> 00:12:44.073
'CAUSE SHE KNOWS SHE GOT
NICK ON THE REBOUND.


272
00:12:44.208 --> 00:12:46.476
SO HE STILL
LIKES YOU?


273
00:12:46.611 --> 00:12:47.543
ARE YOU SERIOUS?

274
00:12:47.679 --> 00:12:49.879
THAT WAS
A HUNDRED YEARS AGO.


275
00:12:49.948 --> 00:12:51.614
[LAUGHING]:
STOP IT...


276
00:12:51.683 --> 00:12:52.615
I'M JUST SAYING.

277
00:12:52.750 --> 00:12:53.750
WELL, I'M HUNGRY,

278
00:12:53.752 --> 00:12:55.150
SO LET'S GO GET
SOME ICE CREAM.


279
00:12:55.186 --> 00:12:56.686
YOU CAN WATCH
YOUR WIFE GET FAT.


280
00:12:56.688 --> 00:12:57.720
- WITH PICKLES?
- YEAH!


281
00:13:08.700 --> 00:13:09.766
MOM...

282
00:13:09.768 --> 00:13:10.766
HI, HONEY.

283
00:13:10.802 --> 00:13:11.767
STOP...

284
00:13:11.836 --> 00:13:13.236
WHY DON'T YOU DO THIS?

285
00:13:13.238 --> 00:13:14.970
YOU'RE A LOT BETTER
AT IT THAN I AM.


286
00:13:15.040 --> 00:13:17.140
OKAY.

287
00:13:20.812 --> 00:13:22.378
SO, YOU GOT A BIG JOB
AHEAD OF YOU.


288
00:13:22.513 --> 00:13:23.779
MM
-HM.

289
00:13:23.848 --> 00:13:28.117
JOHN'S GOING TO BE
TIRED AND STRESSED OUT,


290
00:13:28.153 --> 00:13:32.255
AND HE'S GOING TO
NEED A GOOD WIFE.


291
00:13:32.390 --> 00:13:34.390
DO YOU UNDERSTAND
WHAT I'M SAYING?


292
00:13:36.328 --> 00:13:38.327
YEAH.

293
00:13:38.396 --> 00:13:39.795
YOU DON'T THINK I CAN DO THIS.

294
00:13:39.864 --> 00:13:43.266
I THINK
THAT MARRIAGE IS HARD WORK,


295
00:13:43.268 --> 00:13:44.867
AND IT HELPS TO HAVE
A HAPPY BOSS.


296
00:13:47.338 --> 00:13:50.206
HONEY, YOU'RE MY DAUGHTER,
AND I LOVE YOU,


297
00:13:50.275 --> 00:13:52.674
BUT YOU HAVE TO REALIZE
YOU'RE NOT NUMBER ONE ANYMORE.


298
00:13:52.711 --> 00:13:54.944
YOU'VE GOT TO TAKE
CARE OF YOUR HUSBAND,


299
00:13:55.079 --> 00:13:57.113
AND YOU'VE GOT
A BABY ON THE WAY.


300
00:13:59.617 --> 00:14:00.950
YOU THINK I'M SPOILED.

301
00:14:02.687 --> 00:14:04.754
I THINK YOU'RE 17...

302
00:14:06.024 --> 00:14:07.223
AND THIS IS A JOB
FOR A WOMAN...


303
00:14:07.358 --> 00:14:10.092
[VOICE BREAKING]:
AND YOU'RE JUST A GIRL.


304
00:14:10.161 --> 00:14:11.894
MOM...

305
00:14:11.930 --> 00:14:14.230
SO I JUST
WANT YOU TO...


306
00:14:14.232 --> 00:14:15.564
JUST GROW UP FAST,
OKAY?


307
00:14:15.633 --> 00:14:17.166
FOR EVERYBODY'S SAKE.

308
00:14:17.235 --> 00:14:18.567
OKAY?

309
00:14:18.603 --> 00:14:20.169
PLEASE COME WITH ME.

310
00:14:20.304 --> 00:14:23.539
OH, BABY...

311
00:14:23.541 --> 00:14:25.374
I WISH I COULD.

312
00:14:25.410 --> 00:14:29.044
I'M GOING TO BE FINE.

313
00:14:29.114 --> 00:14:30.780
[♪♪]

314
00:14:37.322 --> 00:14:38.421
THOUGHT YOU MIGHT LIKE THIS.

315
00:14:43.795 --> 00:14:45.060
THAT'S GREAT, MOM.

316
00:14:45.130 --> 00:14:47.830
THANKS.

317
00:14:52.804 --> 00:14:54.871
YOU BELONG THERE, JOHN.

318
00:14:55.006 --> 00:14:57.707
YOU REMEMBER THAT.

319
00:15:03.882 --> 00:15:06.682
BETTER GET GOING.

320
00:15:10.488 --> 00:15:11.854
BYE.

321
00:15:27.505 --> 00:15:29.672
[♪♪]

322
00:15:53.865 --> 00:15:55.130
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

323
00:15:55.200 --> 00:15:56.265
THIS IS AWESOME.
I LOVE IT.


324
00:15:56.400 --> 00:15:58.200
WHAT NUMBER ARE WE?

325
00:15:58.269 --> 00:16:00.002
I THINK 9.
RIGHT THERE!


326
00:16:00.038 --> 00:16:01.671
PERFECT.

327
00:16:01.673 --> 00:16:03.473
GORGEOUS DAY FOR YOU GUYS
TO COME TO BOSTON,


328
00:16:03.608 --> 00:16:04.874
I CAN TELL YOU THAT MUCH.

329
00:16:04.876 --> 00:16:07.075
WELL, HERE WE GO, GUYS,

330
00:16:07.111 --> 00:16:08.611
WELCOME TO YOUR HUMBLE ABODE.

331
00:16:08.680 --> 00:16:10.145
BEDROOM'S JUST IN HERE.

332
00:16:10.181 --> 00:16:13.749
I'LL TAKE YOU
INTO THE LIVING ROOM.


333
00:16:13.785 --> 00:16:15.351
PRETTY BRIGHT, HUH, GUYS?

334
00:16:15.486 --> 00:16:16.485
IT'S AMAZING.

335
00:16:16.554 --> 00:16:19.622
LET ME SHOW YOU
THE BEST PART.


336
00:16:21.759 --> 00:16:23.759
OH...

337
00:16:23.895 --> 00:16:25.127
PRETTY NICE, HUH?

338
00:16:29.300 --> 00:16:30.433
[KNOCKING]

339
00:16:35.273 --> 00:16:36.372
[DEAN FROST]: "DEAR JOHN,

340
00:16:36.441 --> 00:16:38.908
AS DEAN OF FRESHMEN,
IT IS MY DUTY TO INFORM YOU


341
00:16:38.977 --> 00:16:42.111
OF THE COLLEGE'S POSITION
ON YOUR NEW CIRCUMSTANCES.


342
00:16:42.113 --> 00:16:45.114
WHILE THE FIRST YEAR OF COLLEGE
CAN BE A STRESSFUL EXPERIENCE,


343
00:16:45.249 --> 00:16:47.916
YOUR MARITAL STATUS
WILL MAKE IT EVEN MORE SO.


344
00:16:47.952 --> 00:16:49.718
TO THAT END,
PLEASE BEAR IN MIND


345
00:16:49.787 --> 00:16:52.854
THAT YOUR SCHOLARSHIP
IS CONTINGENT ON PASSING GRADES.


346
00:16:52.891 --> 00:16:54.056
FAIL ANY COURSE,

347
00:16:54.191 --> 00:16:58.727
AND HARVARD WILL BE OBLIGED
TO RECONSIDER ITS OPTIONS.


348
00:16:58.763 --> 00:17:00.129
SINCERELY, DEAN FROST."

349
00:17:00.131 --> 00:17:01.797
WELCOME HOME, JOHN.

350
00:17:01.833 --> 00:17:03.399
THIS IS GREAT.

351
00:17:03.534 --> 00:17:04.600
CHEERS.

352
00:17:04.636 --> 00:17:05.668
BYE, THANK YOU.

353
00:17:05.803 --> 00:17:07.069
ANY QUESTIONS,
LET ME KNOW.


354
00:17:07.138 --> 00:17:08.504
[CHUCKLES]

355
00:17:15.546 --> 00:17:19.081
WELCOME TO CALCULUS 101
AND THE REALM OF THE INFINITE.


356
00:17:19.150 --> 00:17:20.749
STARTING TODAY,

357
00:17:20.785 --> 00:17:22.551
THERE ARE NO LIMITS,

358
00:17:22.554 --> 00:17:24.754
JUST POSSIBILITIES.

359
00:17:24.889 --> 00:17:27.089
CALCULUS IS A GATEWAY
TO THE UNKNOWN.


360
00:17:27.091 --> 00:17:30.092
IT PRESUPPOSES CHANGE
AND CHARTS ITS COURSE.


361
00:17:30.227 --> 00:17:32.294
WITH THE DISCOVERY
OF CALCULUS,


362
00:17:32.297 --> 00:17:33.563
ISAAC NEWTON
TRACED THE PLANETS


363
00:17:33.698 --> 00:17:35.030
THROUGH
THE NIGHT SKY.


364
00:17:35.066 --> 00:17:37.433
IT OPENED
NEW WORLDS FOR HIM,


365
00:17:37.568 --> 00:17:39.302
AND IT WILL
FOR YOU TOO.


366
00:17:44.542 --> 00:17:45.507
HI.

367
00:17:45.577 --> 00:17:47.376
HEY.

368
00:17:49.047 --> 00:17:50.346
I KNOW YOU.

369
00:17:52.450 --> 00:17:53.515
YOU'RE THE GUY
IN THE FRONT ROW


370
00:17:53.585 --> 00:17:54.517
WHO NEVER BLINKS.

371
00:17:54.652 --> 00:17:57.520
WELL, I CAN'T AFFORD
TO MISS ANYTHING.


372
00:17:57.522 --> 00:17:58.520
MM
-HM.

373
00:17:58.556 --> 00:17:59.688
DO YOU HAVE A CARD?

374
00:17:59.724 --> 00:18:00.922
YEAH.

375
00:18:00.959 --> 00:18:02.992
PROFESSOR KOWAL,

376
00:18:02.994 --> 00:18:04.593
WHAT A TOOL.

377
00:18:04.662 --> 00:18:06.328
RIGHT?

378
00:18:06.397 --> 00:18:07.996
I'M JAKE.

379
00:18:08.032 --> 00:18:09.331
THAT'S DANNY.

380
00:18:09.367 --> 00:18:10.332
HEY, MAN...

381
00:18:10.401 --> 00:18:12.468
JOHN PATTON.

382
00:18:12.537 --> 00:18:14.070
WHAT DORM ARE
YOU IN, JOHN PATTON?


383
00:18:14.072 --> 00:18:16.472
WELL, I'M NOT ACTUALLY
IN A DORM.


384
00:18:16.474 --> 00:18:18.207
OH! [LAUGHS]

385
00:18:18.276 --> 00:18:19.742
YOU'RE MARRIED.

386
00:18:21.479 --> 00:18:23.211
NO OFFENSE, BUT WHY?

387
00:18:23.247 --> 00:18:25.814
SEEMED LIKE THE BEST IDEA.

388
00:18:25.883 --> 00:18:27.216
OH YEAH?

389
00:18:27.351 --> 00:18:29.085
WHAT HAPPENED,
GET HER PREGNANT?


390
00:18:30.755 --> 00:18:31.954
YEAH.

391
00:18:32.023 --> 00:18:33.489
SO YOU DO BLINK.

392
00:18:35.359 --> 00:18:36.625
WOW, MARRIED
WITH A BABY,


393
00:18:36.628 --> 00:18:39.161
AND KOWAL
FOR CALCULUS.


394
00:18:39.163 --> 00:18:41.697
HEY...

395
00:18:41.766 --> 00:18:43.366
YOU NEED THESE MORE THAN I DO.

396
00:18:45.370 --> 00:18:46.168
LATER.

397
00:18:46.303 --> 00:18:49.238
THANKS.

398
00:18:53.711 --> 00:18:55.177
HEY...

399
00:18:55.179 --> 00:18:56.045
HEY.

400
00:18:56.180 --> 00:18:57.112
WHERE YOU BEEN
IN THIS HEAT?


401
00:18:57.148 --> 00:18:58.180
I WAS STARTING
TO GET WORRIED.


402
00:18:58.216 --> 00:18:59.314
TA DA!

403
00:18:59.384 --> 00:19:00.783
LOOK WHAT I BOUGHT.

404
00:19:00.852 --> 00:19:02.518
WE CAN'T AFFORD THAT.

405
00:19:02.520 --> 00:19:04.787
WELL, WE CAN
WITH MY NEW JOB.


406
00:19:06.857 --> 00:19:07.923
NEW JOB?
WHAT...


407
00:19:07.959 --> 00:19:09.392
I'M A BANK TELLER.

408
00:19:09.527 --> 00:19:11.460
I START NEXT WEEK.

409
00:19:11.529 --> 00:19:13.195
A TELLER?

410
00:19:13.197 --> 00:19:14.330
WHAT?

411
00:19:14.465 --> 00:19:16.865
I GOT SICK OF SITTING AT HOME
ALL DAY, AND...


412
00:19:16.901 --> 00:19:18.133
YOU KNOW,

413
00:19:18.202 --> 00:19:19.735
I WANT TO
CONTRIBUTE, OKAY?


414
00:19:19.737 --> 00:19:21.804
IT'S IMPORTANT TO ME.

415
00:19:23.875 --> 00:19:25.941
SO...

416
00:19:25.977 --> 00:19:28.677
HAVE YOU GOTTEN YOUR
CALC. TEST BACK YET?


417
00:19:28.680 --> 00:19:31.480
NOT YET.

418
00:19:33.417 --> 00:19:34.616
[LAUGHING]

419
00:19:34.652 --> 00:19:36.619
SHE ONLY KICKS
FOR YOU.


420
00:19:36.754 --> 00:19:38.354
WAIT, "SHE?"

421
00:19:38.489 --> 00:19:40.089
YEAH, IT'S A GIRL.

422
00:19:40.224 --> 00:19:42.892
I CAN TELL.

423
00:19:43.027 --> 00:19:45.293
A LITTLE GIRL.

424
00:19:45.329 --> 00:19:47.229
AMANDA ROSE...

425
00:19:47.231 --> 00:19:49.297
AMANDA ROSE PATTON.

426
00:19:49.333 --> 00:19:51.100
AMANDA ROSE...

427
00:19:51.169 --> 00:19:52.101
YOU LIKE IT?

428
00:19:52.236 --> 00:19:53.969
I LOVE IT.

429
00:20:01.212 --> 00:20:02.377
OH, YOU HAVE TO PUT
THE QUARTERS IN


430
00:20:02.413 --> 00:20:03.578
UPSIDE DOWN.

431
00:20:03.614 --> 00:20:04.847
REALLY?

432
00:20:04.916 --> 00:20:06.248
YEAH.

433
00:20:08.519 --> 00:20:09.518
THANK YOU!

434
00:20:09.520 --> 00:20:10.586
[CHUCKLES]

435
00:20:10.655 --> 00:20:11.721
I WOULD NEVER HAVE
FIGURED THAT OUT.


436
00:20:11.856 --> 00:20:13.455
JUST DON'T TELL
JENNY TIPPENS IN 2-F.


437
00:20:13.491 --> 00:20:15.056
SHE ALWAYS FORGETS
TO CHECK FOR COLOR CRAYONS


438
00:20:15.093 --> 00:20:16.592
IN HER SON'S PANTS.

439
00:20:16.594 --> 00:20:17.859
OH, GOD.

440
00:20:17.895 --> 00:20:20.262
I FORGOT TO CHECK THE POCKETS.

441
00:20:20.298 --> 00:20:22.198
I'M HOPELESS.

442
00:20:22.200 --> 00:20:23.532
YOU'RE THE NEW GUYS
ON THE THIRD FLOOR, RIGHT?


443
00:20:23.534 --> 00:20:24.867
YEAH, THAT'S US.

444
00:20:24.869 --> 00:20:26.201
I'M KATHY, BY THE WAY.

445
00:20:26.270 --> 00:20:27.068
BEV.

446
00:20:27.105 --> 00:20:28.003
NICE TO MEET YOU.

447
00:20:28.139 --> 00:20:29.070
I'VE BEEN MEANING
TO STOP BY.


448
00:20:29.107 --> 00:20:32.007
I MANAGE THE BUILDING
WITH MY HUSBAND, TIM.


449
00:20:32.043 --> 00:20:33.142
THE GARBAGE DISPOSAL
IN YOUR UNIT


450
00:20:33.211 --> 00:20:36.745
SOMETIMES THINKS
IT'S ON VACATION,


451
00:20:36.748 --> 00:20:38.214
SO IF YOU HAVE
ANY TROUBLE,


452
00:20:38.216 --> 00:20:39.214
YOU JUST...

453
00:20:39.250 --> 00:20:40.282
IS EVERYTHING OKAY?

454
00:20:44.622 --> 00:20:46.689
YEAH.

455
00:20:53.230 --> 00:20:55.497
IN HIS OWN GRANDIOSE WAY,

456
00:20:55.533 --> 00:20:57.833
SHAKESPEARE WAS A WRITER
OF NARROW SCOPE.


457
00:20:57.835 --> 00:21:00.369
THE COMMON MAN WAS OFTEN
INCIDENTAL TO HIM.


458
00:21:00.371 --> 00:21:03.773
TODAY'S FINAL ESSAY WILL SPEAK
TO THE CONTEMPORARY HERO


459
00:21:03.908 --> 00:21:06.108
AND HOW HE DIFFERS
FROM SHAKESPEARE'S.


460
00:21:06.177 --> 00:21:09.911
ARE HEROES TODAY STILL HAMSTRUNG
BY CLASS DISTINCTION,


461
00:21:09.947 --> 00:21:13.315
OR DO THEY WALK AMONG US,
UNHEARD AND UNSUNG?


462
00:21:13.384 --> 00:21:16.785
IN YOUR READING ASSIGNMENT
ON IAGO TONIGHT,


463
00:21:16.788 --> 00:21:18.320
CONSIDER THIS QUESTION:

464
00:21:18.356 --> 00:21:19.988
THERE WAS THIS
AMAZING DISCUSSION


465
00:21:20.057 --> 00:21:21.190
IN SHAKESPEARE TODAY

466
00:21:21.259 --> 00:21:23.592
COMPARING NIXON
TO IAGO.


467
00:21:23.594 --> 00:21:24.660
THAT CLASS HAS GOTTEN
BETTER AND BETTER


468
00:21:24.662 --> 00:21:26.128
EVERY WEEK.

469
00:21:26.130 --> 00:21:27.129
COOL.

470
00:21:27.264 --> 00:21:28.797
SO...

471
00:21:28.866 --> 00:21:30.199
YOU'RE DOING OKAY IN IT?

472
00:21:30.334 --> 00:21:32.534
I'M ACING IT, ACTUALLY.

473
00:21:32.537 --> 00:21:33.535
REALLY?

474
00:21:33.571 --> 00:21:35.337
MM
-HM.

475
00:21:35.406 --> 00:21:37.939
ARE YOU SURE?

476
00:21:37.975 --> 00:21:40.609
JOHN...

477
00:21:40.744 --> 00:21:42.278
I WAS DOING LAUNDRY

478
00:21:42.280 --> 00:21:44.546
THE OTHER DAY...

479
00:21:44.549 --> 00:21:49.084
AND I FOUND
YOUR CALC TEST.


480
00:21:49.153 --> 00:21:50.853
YOU TOLD ME YOU GOT A B
- ON IT.

481
00:21:53.324 --> 00:21:55.891
LOOK, I'M SORRY, OKAY?

482
00:21:55.960 --> 00:21:58.694
I WAS EMBARRASSED.

483
00:21:58.696 --> 00:21:59.761
I FELT LIKE A FAILURE.

484
00:21:59.831 --> 00:22:01.830
YOU DON'T HAVE TO APOLOGIZE.

485
00:22:01.866 --> 00:22:03.966
DOING BADLY ON A TEST

486
00:22:04.101 --> 00:22:06.768
DOESN'T MAKE YOU
A FAILURE.


487
00:22:06.804 --> 00:22:09.572
YOU NEED TO RELAX, OKAY?

488
00:22:09.707 --> 00:22:11.373
YOU'RE SETTING THE BAR
TOO HIGH.


489
00:22:15.079 --> 00:22:16.645
TRUST ME.

490
00:22:16.681 --> 00:22:18.780
OKAY?

491
00:22:18.816 --> 00:22:20.316
I'LL UNDERSTAND.

492
00:22:26.390 --> 00:22:27.456
COME ON, LET'S
GO FOR A WALK.


493
00:22:27.591 --> 00:22:30.559
WE CAN CLEAN THIS
STUFF UP LATER.


494
00:22:36.868 --> 00:22:39.501
[♪♪]

495
00:22:55.353 --> 00:22:58.220
[SIGHS HEAVILY AND THROWS PENCIL
DOWN IN FRUSTRATION]


496
00:23:18.309 --> 00:23:19.908
TALKED TO BETH.

497
00:23:19.944 --> 00:23:21.643
THEY'RE ALL PLANNING
TO GO CAROLING AGAIN,


498
00:23:21.679 --> 00:23:22.844
JUST LIKE
LAST CHRISTMAS EVE.


499
00:23:22.880 --> 00:23:25.381
AW...

500
00:23:25.516 --> 00:23:28.183
DO YOU REMEMBER
HOW MUCH FUN THAT WAS?


501
00:23:28.219 --> 00:23:31.119
WELL, THEY SAID THAT IT WON'T BE
THE SAME WITHOUT US


502
00:23:31.155 --> 00:23:32.788
AND THEY'LL MISS OUR HARMONIES

503
00:23:32.790 --> 00:23:34.990
AND MY SOLO ON SILENT NIGHT.

504
00:23:35.125 --> 00:23:36.225
OH, I LOVED THAT.

505
00:23:38.262 --> 00:23:40.729
OH, UM, I WAS WATCHING TV
THE OTHER DAY,


506
00:23:40.864 --> 00:23:42.397
AND, UM...

507
00:23:42.466 --> 00:23:44.066
WELL, THERE'S THIS
HOTEL IN BOSTON.


508
00:23:44.201 --> 00:23:46.268
IT'S REALLY CHEAP,
AND NICE,


509
00:23:46.270 --> 00:23:48.336
AND THEY EVEN GIVE YOU
BREAKFAST IN BED,


510
00:23:48.372 --> 00:23:50.205
AND GUESS WHAT ELSE?

511
00:23:50.241 --> 00:23:51.140
WHAT?

512
00:23:51.275 --> 00:23:53.475
I SAVED UP ENOUGH
MONEY FROM MY JOB


513
00:23:53.477 --> 00:23:55.411
SO WE CAN SPEND
THE NIGHT THERE


514
00:23:55.546 --> 00:23:56.611
OVER THE HOLIDAYS,

515
00:23:56.647 --> 00:23:58.213
SINCE WE CAN'T
AFFORD TO GO HOME.


516
00:23:58.249 --> 00:23:59.882
THEY DOUBLED MY HOURS
AT THE BOOK STORE.


517
00:23:59.884 --> 00:24:00.883
REALLY?

518
00:24:01.018 --> 00:24:02.551
I WORK EVERY DAY
BUT CHRISTMAS.


519
00:24:02.620 --> 00:24:05.621
SO YOU CAN'T GET AWAY,
JUST FOR ONE NIGHT?


520
00:24:05.623 --> 00:24:08.023
[SIGHING]:
I'M SORRY.


521
00:24:08.025 --> 00:24:09.091
I PROMISED, YOU KNOW?

522
00:24:09.160 --> 00:24:10.159
IT'S OKAY.

523
00:24:10.161 --> 00:24:12.694
NO, WE NEED
THE MONEY.


524
00:24:12.697 --> 00:24:13.695
I'M OFF
TO THE LIBRARY,


525
00:24:13.731 --> 00:24:14.830
I'M MEETING A GUY
FROM CALC.


526
00:24:14.832 --> 00:24:16.799
TO PREP FOR THE FINAL.

527
00:24:19.436 --> 00:24:21.503
I'LL BE HOME LATE.

528
00:24:21.572 --> 00:24:23.572
I LOVE YOU!

529
00:25:43.020 --> 00:25:44.586
THANK YOU, MR. PATTON.

530
00:25:44.721 --> 00:25:46.021
THANK YOU.

531
00:25:49.259 --> 00:25:52.995
[LAUGHING AND CHATTING]

532
00:25:53.130 --> 00:25:56.131
OKAY, REMIND ME AGAIN,
JUST ONE LAST TIME.


533
00:25:56.133 --> 00:25:57.398
ALL RIGHT, JAKE
IS FROM NEW YORK.


534
00:25:57.435 --> 00:25:58.534
JAKE, YES.

535
00:25:58.536 --> 00:25:59.468
DANNY IS
FROM CLEVELAND.


536
00:25:59.537 --> 00:26:00.536
RIGHT.

537
00:26:00.538 --> 00:26:01.470
AND DANNY'S BRINGING
HIS GIRLFRIEND.


538
00:26:01.539 --> 00:26:02.471
SHE'S VERY NICE,

539
00:26:02.606 --> 00:26:04.606
BUT NOT NEARLY
AS PRETTY AS YOU.


540
00:26:04.741 --> 00:26:07.342
SHE'S NOT NEARLY
AS PREGNANT, EITHER.


541
00:26:07.344 --> 00:26:11.213
OKAY, PROFESSOR, MRS. KOWAL,
CHRISTMAS PARTY.


542
00:26:11.215 --> 00:26:12.448
I CAN DO THIS.

543
00:26:15.819 --> 00:26:16.818
HELLO.
MERRY CHRISTMAS.


544
00:26:16.887 --> 00:26:17.886
HI!

545
00:26:17.888 --> 00:26:18.887
HI.
HOW YOU DOING?


546
00:26:18.923 --> 00:26:19.888
GOOD.

547
00:26:19.957 --> 00:26:21.623
PLEASE, COME IN.

548
00:26:21.625 --> 00:26:24.326
THIS IS
MY WIFE, KATHY.


549
00:26:24.328 --> 00:26:26.561
[♪♪]

550
00:26:26.630 --> 00:26:28.430
THE FIRST MONTH
NEARLY KILLED ME,


551
00:26:28.499 --> 00:26:29.631
BUT THEN I GOT
THE HANG OF IT.


552
00:26:29.700 --> 00:26:30.766
MM, NOT ME.

553
00:26:30.901 --> 00:26:32.434
MAN, THE FINAL,
WHAT WAS THAT?


554
00:26:32.503 --> 00:26:33.768
IT WAS BULL.

555
00:26:33.838 --> 00:26:35.637
DID WE EVEN COVER
HALF OF THAT STUFF?


556
00:26:35.639 --> 00:26:37.840
DON'T YOU GET
TIRED AT WORK?


557
00:26:37.975 --> 00:26:39.374
NO, NOT REALLY.

558
00:26:39.443 --> 00:26:40.709
I MEAN,
THE TELLER WINDOW


559
00:26:40.711 --> 00:26:41.910
KEEPS GETTING
FURTHER AWAY,


560
00:26:41.979 --> 00:26:43.645
BUT OTHER THAN THAT,
I'M FINE,


561
00:26:43.647 --> 00:26:45.847
AND, WELL, I'M GOING TO QUIT
AS SOON AS SHE'S BORN,


562
00:26:45.883 --> 00:26:47.783
'CAUSE SHE'LL COME FIRST.

563
00:26:47.785 --> 00:26:49.317
IT WAS IN THE OPTIONAL
HOMEWORK, GUYS.


564
00:26:49.353 --> 00:26:50.452
YOU ACTUALLY
DID THAT?


565
00:26:50.521 --> 00:26:51.587
UM...

566
00:26:51.722 --> 00:26:52.721
EXCUSE ME,

567
00:26:52.723 --> 00:26:54.055
CAN I BORROW YOUR FRIEND
FOR A MOMENT?


568
00:26:54.125 --> 00:26:56.525
I'LL BRING HIM
RIGHT BACK, I PROMISE.


569
00:26:56.660 --> 00:26:57.593
YOU DO THAT, TOO?

570
00:26:57.728 --> 00:26:59.127
YEAH, HOME-COOKED MEAL
EVERY NIGHT.


571
00:26:59.130 --> 00:27:01.062
YOU ARE SUCH A GROWNUP.

572
00:27:01.098 --> 00:27:02.664
THANK YOU.

573
00:27:13.210 --> 00:27:15.744
I DEBATED WHETHER
TO TELL YOU THIS TONIGHT,


574
00:27:15.879 --> 00:27:18.747
BUT YOU HAVE TO REGISTER
FOR SPRING CLASSES SOON,


575
00:27:18.816 --> 00:27:20.115
AND WHAT I HAVE TO SAY
WILL AFFECT THAT.


576
00:27:21.886 --> 00:27:23.751
YOU FLUNKED THE FINAL, JOHN,

577
00:27:23.787 --> 00:27:24.953
AND SINCE THAT
WAS ONE-HALF


578
00:27:25.088 --> 00:27:26.221
OF YOUR FINAL GRADE,

579
00:27:26.290 --> 00:27:28.223
TECHNICALLY,
YOU FAILED THE COURSE.


580
00:27:28.225 --> 00:27:30.425
I KNOW,

581
00:27:30.461 --> 00:27:31.492
IT MUST COME AS A BLOW.

582
00:27:31.529 --> 00:27:33.562
I KNOW HOW HARD YOU'VE WORKED.

583
00:27:33.631 --> 00:27:36.030
BECAUSE OF THAT
AND YOUR CIRCUMSTANCES AT HOME,


584
00:27:36.066 --> 00:27:38.167
I'VE DECIDED TO
PASS YOU WITH A D,


585
00:27:38.302 --> 00:27:40.502
BUT I STRONGLY ADVISE YOU

586
00:27:40.504 --> 00:27:43.105
TO SIDESTEP CALCULUS
NEXT SEMESTER.


587
00:27:43.240 --> 00:27:44.907
THE COURSE
INTENSIFIES.


588
00:27:48.445 --> 00:27:51.046
JOHN?

589
00:27:51.115 --> 00:27:53.482
THANK YOU.

590
00:27:56.587 --> 00:27:59.254
[GROUP OF CAROLERS SINGING]

591
00:28:03.060 --> 00:28:05.060
NO, WE'RE NOT
GOING TO BE ALONE.


592
00:28:05.062 --> 00:28:06.127
WE'RE, UM...

593
00:28:06.197 --> 00:28:08.397
WE'RE GOING TO BEV AND TIM'S
FOR DINNER.


594
00:28:10.668 --> 00:28:14.736
WILL YOU TAKE A PICTURE
OF THE TREE FOR ME?


595
00:28:14.871 --> 00:28:17.138
YEAH, I LOVE YOU, TOO.

596
00:28:17.174 --> 00:28:19.741
OKAY, BYE.

597
00:28:21.412 --> 00:28:23.745
[SNIFFLING]

598
00:28:27.017 --> 00:28:29.351
MOM SENDS HER LOVE.

599
00:28:29.353 --> 00:28:30.619
OH. HI, MOM.

600
00:28:30.754 --> 00:28:33.021
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

601
00:28:33.156 --> 00:28:37.359
SEMESTER'S OVER.
PUT THIS BOOK AWAY.


602
00:28:37.361 --> 00:28:39.695
I WAS JUST WONDERING
WHAT TO CHARGE.


603
00:28:39.830 --> 00:28:42.230
I'M SELLING IT.

604
00:28:42.266 --> 00:28:43.632
I DECIDED TO DROP CALC.

605
00:28:43.634 --> 00:28:46.234
WHY WOULD YOU DO THAT?

606
00:28:46.270 --> 00:28:47.502
YOU...

607
00:28:47.504 --> 00:28:50.305
JOHN, YOU NEED MATH
FOR BUSINESS SCHOOL, DON'T YOU?


608
00:28:50.374 --> 00:28:51.707
YOU KNOW WHAT,
LET'S TALK ABOUT THIS LATER.


609
00:29:00.784 --> 00:29:02.050
FOR MY WIFE.

610
00:29:02.119 --> 00:29:04.820
ON OUR FIRST CHRISTMAS.

611
00:29:06.857 --> 00:29:08.389
YOU ALREADY GOT ME
THAT GORGEOUS NIGHTGOWN.


612
00:29:08.425 --> 00:29:10.325
GO ON.

613
00:29:10.394 --> 00:29:11.726
WELL...

614
00:29:11.762 --> 00:29:13.128
NOW I FEEL BAD.

615
00:29:13.197 --> 00:29:15.797
ALL I GOT YOU WAS
THAT STUPID SWEATER.


616
00:29:23.607 --> 00:29:25.073
IT'S FOR
AFTER THE BABY,


617
00:29:25.109 --> 00:29:26.875
TO GO HOME.

618
00:29:26.877 --> 00:29:27.875
THE BABY WON'T COST
ANYTHING,


619
00:29:27.911 --> 00:29:29.877
BUT YOU'LL
HAVE TO HOLD HER.


620
00:29:29.913 --> 00:29:31.079
HOW?

621
00:29:31.214 --> 00:29:32.481
WE CAN'T AFFORD THIS.

622
00:29:32.483 --> 00:29:34.950
THE EXTRA SHIFTS
AT THE BOOKSTORE.


623
00:29:35.085 --> 00:29:37.618
OH, MY GOD...

624
00:29:37.655 --> 00:29:41.923
I WANTED TO DO
SOMETHING SPECIAL FOR YOU.


625
00:29:43.627 --> 00:29:46.161
THANK YOU.

626
00:29:46.296 --> 00:29:51.133
MERRY CHRISTMAS,
KATH.


627
00:30:22.733 --> 00:30:26.535
I JUST, I WANT TO GET
TO THE MOVIE EARLY, OKAY?


628
00:30:26.537 --> 00:30:28.536
BECAUSE I WANT AN AISLE SEAT,

629
00:30:28.605 --> 00:30:30.939
BECAUSE IF-IF I DON'T HAVE
ANY ROOM TO STRETCH MY LEGS,


630
00:30:31.008 --> 00:30:32.140
THEY CRAMP UP.

631
00:30:32.142 --> 00:30:33.875
I-I TOLD YOU THAT
SO MANY TIMES.


632
00:30:33.944 --> 00:30:35.943
I WOULDN'T WORRY
ABOUT SEATING TONIGHT.


633
00:30:35.979 --> 00:30:37.011
I MEAN, MOST PEOPLE
AREN'T EVEN BACK


634
00:30:37.047 --> 00:30:38.479
FROM CHRISTMAS BREAK.

635
00:30:38.515 --> 00:30:40.749
ANYWAY,
EVERYONE I KNOW


636
00:30:40.884 --> 00:30:42.084
IS GOING TO
THE TOPHER FLYNN LECTURE.


637
00:30:42.219 --> 00:30:43.418
HE'S SPEAKING
ON GENETIC ENGINEERING.


638
00:30:43.553 --> 00:30:45.420
WELL, WOULD YOU RATHER GO
TO THE LECTURE?


639
00:30:45.555 --> 00:30:47.889
NAH, YOU'D BE BORED.

640
00:30:49.426 --> 00:30:50.826
WHY WOULD I BE BORED?

641
00:30:50.828 --> 00:30:51.893
BECAUSE I'M DUMB?

642
00:30:51.962 --> 00:30:54.228
I WOULDN'T UNDERSTAND
A HARVARD LECTURE?


643
00:30:54.264 --> 00:30:55.630
[CHUCKLES]

644
00:30:55.699 --> 00:30:58.299
YOU'D BE BORED BECAUSE
YOU HAVEN'T BEEN STUDYING FLYNN


645
00:30:58.369 --> 00:30:59.301
ALL SEMESTER LIKE I HAVE.

646
00:30:59.436 --> 00:31:01.703
LISTEN, MISTER HARVARD,

647
00:31:01.838 --> 00:31:04.572
I-I TOOK BIOLOGY
IN SOPHOMORE YEAR,


648
00:31:04.641 --> 00:31:05.707
AND I GOT A B
-PLUS,

649
00:31:05.842 --> 00:31:07.843
AND MR. MERLING SAID
THAT I SHOWED GREAT PROMISE


650
00:31:07.978 --> 00:31:09.044
AS A SCIENTIFIC RESEARCHER!

651
00:31:09.179 --> 00:31:10.178
YOU KNOW WHAT, KATH,

652
00:31:10.247 --> 00:31:11.646
IF YOU'D RATHER
GO TO THE LECTURE,


653
00:31:11.715 --> 00:31:12.781
LET'S JUST GO
TO THE LECTURE.


654
00:31:12.916 --> 00:31:15.716
I DON'T WANT TO GO TO
THE STUPID LECTURE, JOHN!


655
00:31:15.753 --> 00:31:16.651
OKAY?

656
00:31:16.787 --> 00:31:18.786
OKAY.

657
00:31:18.822 --> 00:31:21.523
I JUST WANT YOU

658
00:31:21.592 --> 00:31:23.458
TO ROLL ME INTO AN AISLE SEAT,

659
00:31:23.593 --> 00:31:26.194
WATCH A MOVIE WITH ME,

660
00:31:26.196 --> 00:31:27.996
AND TELL ME I'M PRETTY--

661
00:31:28.131 --> 00:31:29.464
YOU ARE PRETTY.

662
00:31:29.599 --> 00:31:32.334
NO, I'M NOT PRETTY, I'M A MESS!

663
00:31:32.336 --> 00:31:35.637
I'M AN ANGRY, BAD MESS!

664
00:31:37.875 --> 00:31:41.243
I USED TO BE CUTE,
AND-AND NICE, AND SKINNY...


665
00:31:43.414 --> 00:31:47.349
I HAVE TO HAVE
THIS BABY SOON, JOHN, OKAY?


666
00:31:47.484 --> 00:31:49.484
I'M STARTING TO LOSE
MY SENSE OF HUMOR.


667
00:31:53.524 --> 00:31:55.290
[SNIFFLES AND SIGHS]

668
00:32:07.905 --> 00:32:11.039
<i>...I CAN'T BELIEVE
WHAT YOU DO HERE.</i>


669
00:32:11.108 --> 00:32:13.642
<i>I'VE DREAMED ABOUT IT
SO LONG.</i>


670
00:32:13.777 --> 00:32:15.510
<i>A LIFETIME...</i>

671
00:32:15.546 --> 00:32:18.914
ARE YOU STILL
MAD AT ME?


672
00:32:18.916 --> 00:32:21.649
MM
-MM.

673
00:32:21.685 --> 00:32:23.251
THEN EASE UP
ON THE GRIP.


674
00:32:23.386 --> 00:32:26.854
YOU'RE MAKING
MY HAND GO NUMB.


675
00:32:26.890 --> 00:32:28.523
WELL, UNLESS YOU WANT
YOUR HAND BROKEN,


676
00:32:28.525 --> 00:32:30.859
YOU BETTER GET ME
OUT OF HERE NOW.


677
00:32:30.994 --> 00:32:33.394
YOUR LEGS
CRAMPING AGAIN?


678
00:32:33.430 --> 00:32:34.996
[GASPING]:
I CAN'T TELL.


679
00:32:35.032 --> 00:32:36.931
THE CONTRACTIONS
ARE TOO MUCH.


680
00:32:37.000 --> 00:32:39.000
CONTRACTIONS?

681
00:32:39.036 --> 00:32:42.137
I THINK SO.

682
00:32:44.208 --> 00:32:46.207
OKAY...

683
00:32:46.243 --> 00:32:48.143
[GASPING]

684
00:32:48.145 --> 00:32:49.878
WAIT...

685
00:32:49.880 --> 00:32:52.480
GOT IT, GOT IT.

686
00:32:52.516 --> 00:32:54.816
WHY DIDN'T YOU SAY
YOU WERE IN LABOR?


687
00:32:54.885 --> 00:32:56.284
I DON'T KNOW,
YOU JUST SEEMED


688
00:32:56.286 --> 00:32:57.418
SO WRAPPED UP
IN THE MOVIE.


689
00:32:57.454 --> 00:32:58.419
YOU HAD TEARS
IN YOUR EYES.


690
00:32:58.489 --> 00:32:59.554
THAT'S 'CAUSE YOU WERE
CRUSHING MY HAND!


691
00:32:59.590 --> 00:33:00.755
I GOT TO CALL JAKE.

692
00:33:00.891 --> 00:33:02.223
HE'S DRIVING US
TO THE HOSPITAL.


693
00:33:02.259 --> 00:33:03.625
OKAY. DO THAT.

694
00:33:03.694 --> 00:33:05.760
NO, NO, NO, ISN'T HE
AT THE LECTURE?


695
00:33:05.762 --> 00:33:07.562
I'LL CALL DANNY,
HE CAN GET JAKE'S CAR.


696
00:33:07.697 --> 00:33:09.164
OKAY. OKAY.

697
00:33:09.299 --> 00:33:10.365
[BREATHING DELIBERATELY]

698
00:33:10.500 --> 00:33:11.600
DANNY!

699
00:33:18.175 --> 00:33:19.641
WHAT TOOK YOU
SO LONG?


700
00:33:19.710 --> 00:33:20.975
COME ON!

701
00:33:21.044 --> 00:33:22.444
COME ON.

702
00:33:22.446 --> 00:33:24.179
NO, NO, NO, JOHN,
I AM NOT GETTING IN THAT THING.


703
00:33:24.181 --> 00:33:25.846
NO, IT'LL BE--

704
00:33:25.883 --> 00:33:27.048
[SCREAMING IN PAIN]

705
00:33:27.183 --> 00:33:28.583
COULD YOU PLEASE
DO ME A HUGE FAVOR


706
00:33:28.585 --> 00:33:29.784
AND DO NOT HAVE A BABY
IN THIS CAR?


707
00:33:29.853 --> 00:33:30.852
DANNY, COME ON!

708
00:33:30.854 --> 00:33:31.986
JAKE'S
OBSESSIVELY NEAT.


709
00:33:32.022 --> 00:33:32.987
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

710
00:33:33.056 --> 00:33:34.723
GET OUT OF FIRST!
PUT IT IN SECOND!


711
00:33:34.725 --> 00:33:35.790
[STAMMERING]:
UH, SECOND, RIGHT.


712
00:33:35.792 --> 00:33:36.858
DANNY!

713
00:33:36.860 --> 00:33:37.926
UH, STUPID QUESTION,

714
00:33:37.995 --> 00:33:40.061
BUT WHAT EXACTLY
IS SECOND?


715
00:33:40.063 --> 00:33:42.463
[PANTING]

716
00:33:42.533 --> 00:33:44.799
KEEP BREATHING.

717
00:33:44.835 --> 00:33:46.467
DO THE FOUR
RAPID EXHALES,


718
00:33:46.537 --> 00:33:48.737
AND THEN ONE SLOW.

719
00:33:48.739 --> 00:33:51.806
EXHALE AND BLOW.

720
00:33:51.808 --> 00:33:54.008
GOOD. GOOD.

721
00:33:54.044 --> 00:33:56.077
OKAY...

722
00:33:56.079 --> 00:33:58.279
JUST TALK TO ME, OKAY?

723
00:33:58.315 --> 00:33:59.881
TELL ME I'LL BE A GOOD MOM.

724
00:34:00.016 --> 00:34:01.616
YOU'LL BE THE BEST.

725
00:34:01.751 --> 00:34:03.919
[BREATHING REGULARLY]

726
00:34:06.289 --> 00:34:07.989
YOU'RE DOING
GOOD...


727
00:34:11.929 --> 00:34:14.563
[BABY CRYING]

728
00:34:22.973 --> 00:34:25.773
THE DOCTOR WANTS TO
RUN A FEW TESTS.


729
00:34:25.809 --> 00:34:26.774
IT'S STANDARD STUFF,

730
00:34:26.843 --> 00:34:29.577
YOU GOT NOTHING
TO WORRY ABOUT, OKAY?


731
00:34:29.580 --> 00:34:32.113
CONGRATULATIONS, KATHY,
HE'S BEAUTIFUL,


732
00:34:32.182 --> 00:34:34.315
AND I WILL BRING HIM
RIGHT BACK, DAD,


733
00:34:34.351 --> 00:34:35.417
I PROMISE.

734
00:34:43.026 --> 00:34:44.191
DO YOU THINK
HE'LL BE OKAY?


735
00:34:44.227 --> 00:34:46.594
HE'LL BE FINE.

736
00:34:46.630 --> 00:34:48.463
YOU DID GREAT.

737
00:34:48.599 --> 00:34:50.865
HE'S PERFECT.

738
00:34:51.001 --> 00:34:53.000
HE'S PERFECT...

739
00:34:53.036 --> 00:34:56.771
I WAS SO SURE
IT WAS A GIRL.


740
00:34:58.775 --> 00:35:01.209
SO I WAS
THINKING ADAM.


741
00:35:01.211 --> 00:35:03.611
INSTEAD OF
AMANDA ROSE?


742
00:35:03.614 --> 00:35:05.146
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

743
00:35:05.182 --> 00:35:07.148
ADAM...

744
00:35:07.283 --> 00:35:11.619
I THINK WE'RE A FAMILY.

745
00:35:11.688 --> 00:35:14.823
YOU, ME, AND ADAM.

746
00:35:14.825 --> 00:35:17.292
WE'RE OUR OWN
LITTLE FAMILY.


747
00:35:22.499 --> 00:35:23.765
I LOVE YOU.

748
00:35:23.767 --> 00:35:25.767
I LOVE YOU, TOO.

749
00:35:33.043 --> 00:35:34.042
MOM, HE'S TRYING TO TALK--

750
00:35:34.111 --> 00:35:36.244
NO, HE'S NOT HUNGRY, MOM,
I JUST FED HIM,


751
00:35:36.379 --> 00:35:38.980
AND, NO, HE'S NOT WET, EITHER.

752
00:35:39.049 --> 00:35:41.649
OKAY, WELL, IF HE'S TIRED,
THEN WHY DOESN'T HE SLEEP?


753
00:35:41.652 --> 00:35:44.585
I MEAN, I PUT HIM DOWN,
AND HE JUST, HE SCREAMS.


754
00:35:44.655 --> 00:35:46.054
OKAY, SHH, SHH, SHH...

755
00:35:46.123 --> 00:35:47.855
IT'S OKAY...

756
00:35:47.891 --> 00:35:48.923
NO, JOHN, I'M FINE.

757
00:35:48.959 --> 00:35:51.059
KATH, LET ME TRY.

758
00:35:51.194 --> 00:35:53.461
MOM, I'M GOING TO CALL YOU
RIGHT BACK, OKAY?


759
00:35:53.596 --> 00:35:54.996
OKAY, RIGHT.

760
00:35:55.065 --> 00:35:56.197
IT'S OKAY, BABY BOY...

761
00:35:56.199 --> 00:35:57.198
LET HER COME OUT.

762
00:35:57.333 --> 00:35:59.000
SHE WANTS TO HELP.
SHE'S DYING TO.


763
00:35:59.002 --> 00:36:00.534
NO, JOHN, SHE CAN'T AFFORD IT.

764
00:36:00.570 --> 00:36:02.737
I JUST, I WANT TO DO THIS
ON MY OWN, OKAY?


765
00:36:02.806 --> 00:36:04.472
KATH, KATH...

766
00:36:04.474 --> 00:36:05.606
MOMMY'S HERE!
HAPPY!


767
00:36:05.642 --> 00:36:06.541
YOU'RE
EXHAUSTED.


768
00:36:06.676 --> 00:36:07.608
NO, I'M FINE.

769
00:36:07.644 --> 00:36:08.543
YOU'RE NOT
THINKING STRAIGHT.


770
00:36:08.678 --> 00:36:09.610
SHH, SHH, SHH...

771
00:36:09.646 --> 00:36:10.678
HERE,
GIVE HIM HERE.


772
00:36:10.714 --> 00:36:11.813
OKAY--

773
00:36:11.882 --> 00:36:15.950
[CRYING]

774
00:36:15.952 --> 00:36:16.951
HEY, IT'S OKAY, IT'S OKAY.

775
00:36:17.087 --> 00:36:18.019
SHH...

776
00:36:18.154 --> 00:36:19.154
NAP TIME, BABY BOY.

777
00:36:19.156 --> 00:36:23.024
EVEN THE SUN'S
GOING TO SLEEP.


778
00:36:23.026 --> 00:36:24.626
[BABY STOPS CRYING]

779
00:36:26.696 --> 00:36:27.762
I JUST...

780
00:36:27.798 --> 00:36:31.833
I RUBBED HIS BELLY,
AND HE STOPPED CRYING.


781
00:36:31.835 --> 00:36:34.035
HOW LUCKY ARE WE?

782
00:36:34.170 --> 00:36:37.839
OUR KID COMES WITH
AN ON/OFF SWITCH.


783
00:36:54.891 --> 00:36:57.158
DEAN FROST
WILL SEE YOU NOW.


784
00:37:02.599 --> 00:37:04.999
HI, YOU ASKED TO SEE ME?

785
00:37:05.035 --> 00:37:08.970
AH, YES, THE NEW FATHER.

786
00:37:10.507 --> 00:37:11.672
HOW'S THAT GOING?

787
00:37:11.708 --> 00:37:14.142
JUST FINE, THANK YOU.

788
00:37:14.144 --> 00:37:18.012
I'VE BEEN GOING OVER
YOUR TRANSCRIPT, JOHN.


789
00:37:18.081 --> 00:37:20.882
WHY DID YOU DECIDE
TO RISK CALCULUS AGAIN?


790
00:37:21.017 --> 00:37:23.751
BECAUSE IT'S RECOMMENDED
FOR BUSINESS SCHOOL,


791
00:37:23.754 --> 00:37:25.220
AND THAT'S
WHERE I'M HEADED.


792
00:37:25.222 --> 00:37:27.689
BUT I SEE HERE THAT, UM...

793
00:37:27.824 --> 00:37:31.092
PROFESSOR KOWAL
SUGGESTED YOU DROP IT.


794
00:37:31.161 --> 00:37:34.361
THAT WAS HIS OPINION, NOT MINE.

795
00:37:34.397 --> 00:37:36.564
I DON'T WALK AWAY
FROM SOMETHING


796
00:37:36.633 --> 00:37:38.032
JUST BECAUSE
SOMEONE TELLS ME TO.


797
00:37:38.101 --> 00:37:39.300
I LEAVE ON MY OWN TERMS.

798
00:37:43.573 --> 00:37:44.638
COME WITH ME, JOHN.

799
00:37:44.674 --> 00:37:48.309
I HAVE A MEETING
ACROSS CAMPUS.


800
00:37:49.579 --> 00:37:50.845
YOU ENJOY
A CHALLENGE, JOHN?


801
00:37:50.914 --> 00:37:52.447
YOU RISE TO IT?

802
00:37:52.449 --> 00:37:53.915
ALWAYS.

803
00:37:53.917 --> 00:37:54.915
EVEN THE
MIGHTIEST LION


804
00:37:54.951 --> 00:37:56.784
DOES NOT ATTACK
THE ELEPHANT.


805
00:37:56.820 --> 00:37:58.853
WHY IS THAT?

806
00:37:58.922 --> 00:38:00.922
BECAUSE THE ELEPHANT'S
TOO BIG.


807
00:38:01.057 --> 00:38:02.590
THE LION KNOWS
HE CAN'T WIN.


808
00:38:02.659 --> 00:38:03.458
PRECISELY.

809
00:38:03.593 --> 00:38:04.859
KNOW YOUR LIMITATIONS.

810
00:38:04.928 --> 00:38:07.195
THEY DEFINE YOU AS MUCH
AS YOUR TALENTS.


811
00:38:07.330 --> 00:38:08.463
SO DROP CALC.

812
00:38:08.465 --> 00:38:09.530
THAT'S WHAT
YOU'RE SAYING?


813
00:38:09.599 --> 00:38:11.465
I'M SAYING WALK AWAY NOW
AND IT CAN'T HURT YOU.


814
00:38:11.501 --> 00:38:14.202
IS THAT
WHAT YOU DID?


815
00:38:14.271 --> 00:38:15.736
I'M SORRY?

816
00:38:15.772 --> 00:38:17.672
YOU HAVE A PHD IN PHYSICS.

817
00:38:17.741 --> 00:38:18.939
THAT TOOK, WHAT,
FIVE YEARS TO EARN?


818
00:38:18.975 --> 00:38:22.343
SIX, ACTUALLY.

819
00:38:22.345 --> 00:38:23.344
SIX YEARS,

820
00:38:23.479 --> 00:38:24.412
AND IN ALL THAT TIME,

821
00:38:24.547 --> 00:38:26.013
THERE WAS NEVER A THEORY
THAT BAFFLED YOU


822
00:38:26.049 --> 00:38:28.149
OR A PROBLEM THAT
YOU COULDN'T SOLVE?


823
00:38:28.284 --> 00:38:29.217
WELL, OF COURSE THERE WAS.

824
00:38:29.352 --> 00:38:31.953
DID YOU FACE YOUR LIMITATIONS
AND WALK AWAY,


825
00:38:31.955 --> 00:38:34.955
OR DID YOU WORK HARDER
BECAUSE YOU WANTED IT SO BAD,


826
00:38:34.991 --> 00:38:36.424
AND YOU KNEW THE ANSWER
WAS SOMEWHERE IN YOUR HEAD?


827
00:38:36.559 --> 00:38:40.160
I DID STUMBLE,

828
00:38:40.197 --> 00:38:41.562
YOU'RE RIGHT,

829
00:38:41.565 --> 00:38:42.831
BUT IT WAS NEAR THE FINISH LINE,

830
00:38:42.966 --> 00:38:44.765
NOT AT THE START OF THE RACE.

831
00:38:44.835 --> 00:38:46.167
IT DOESN'T MATTER.

832
00:38:46.302 --> 00:38:48.303
EITHER WAY,
YOU HAVE TO GET BACK UP.


833
00:38:50.073 --> 00:38:51.639
THANKS FOR YOUR ADVICE,
DEAN FROST,


834
00:38:51.774 --> 00:38:53.040
BUT I'LL BE BACK
IN PROFESSOR KOWAL'S CLASS


835
00:38:53.109 --> 00:38:54.108
TOMORROW.

836
00:38:54.177 --> 00:38:55.677
FRONT ROW.

837
00:38:58.448 --> 00:39:00.180
THE TALE OF THE LION
AND THE ELEPHANT.


838
00:39:00.217 --> 00:39:01.449
WHAT A CROCK.

839
00:39:01.518 --> 00:39:04.118
YOU KNOW,
ANY LION WORTH HIS SALT


840
00:39:04.187 --> 00:39:05.119
WOULD SCOPE OUT
THE OLDEST ELEPHANT


841
00:39:05.255 --> 00:39:06.254
IN THE HERD,

842
00:39:06.256 --> 00:39:07.455
AND WAIT TILL HE FELL ASLEEP,

843
00:39:07.457 --> 00:39:09.857
AND YOU BET YOUR BUTT
THERE'D BE DUMBO FOR DINNER.


844
00:39:09.860 --> 00:39:11.926
AM I RIGHT?

845
00:39:12.061 --> 00:39:14.395
OF COURSE I AM.

846
00:39:14.397 --> 00:39:17.398
NOT THAT DADDY WOULD EVER,
EVER HURT AN ELEPHANT, OKAY,


847
00:39:17.533 --> 00:39:19.400
BECAUSE THEY'RE GENTLE
AND INTELLIGENT CREATURES.


848
00:39:19.436 --> 00:39:20.534
YOU REMEMBER THAT,

849
00:39:20.604 --> 00:39:23.604
AND BE KIND
TO ANIMALS.


850
00:39:23.607 --> 00:39:25.273
THANKS FOR
LISTENING.


851
00:39:25.408 --> 00:39:26.340
[BABY COOS AND GURGLES]

852
00:39:26.376 --> 00:39:31.045
AND FOR YOUR EXCELLENT
COMMENTARY.


853
00:39:41.725 --> 00:39:42.857
DID YOU HEAR THE BABY?

854
00:39:44.427 --> 00:39:45.693
I DIDN'T HEAR
ANYTHING.


855
00:39:45.729 --> 00:39:47.695
HUH.

856
00:39:47.830 --> 00:39:50.765
I JUST, I WANT TO GET HIM
ON A SCHEDULE, YOU KNOW?


857
00:39:50.900 --> 00:39:53.368
POOR LITTLE GUY'S UP
SUCH WEIRD HOURS.


858
00:39:53.370 --> 00:39:54.768
HE'LL SLEEP LIKE A ROCK
TONIGHT.


859
00:39:54.804 --> 00:39:56.103
OUR LITTLE TRIP
TUCKERED HIM OUT.


860
00:39:56.139 --> 00:39:57.838
HE CAME WITH ME

861
00:39:57.874 --> 00:39:58.973
TO TURN IN MY ECONOMICS PAPER

862
00:39:58.975 --> 00:40:00.308
WHILE YOU WERE
AT THE STORE TODAY.


863
00:40:02.579 --> 00:40:03.645
YOU TOOK HIM OUT?

864
00:40:04.981 --> 00:40:06.914
IN THIS WEATHER?

865
00:40:06.950 --> 00:40:07.982
I BUNDLED HIM UP IN THAT THING
YOUR AUNT JOAN SENT.


866
00:40:08.018 --> 00:40:09.183
HE WAS FINE.

867
00:40:09.219 --> 00:40:11.853
YEAH, OKAY, BUT DID YOU
PUT ON HIS LITTLE BOOTIES?


868
00:40:11.988 --> 00:40:13.254
DID YOU MAKE SURE
HIS FEET WERE COVERED?


869
00:40:13.256 --> 00:40:15.590
NO, I MADE HIM WALK BAREFOOT
THROUGH THE SNOW.


870
00:40:17.860 --> 00:40:18.993
IT'S NOT FUNNY, JOHN.

871
00:40:20.330 --> 00:40:22.130
GOD...

872
00:40:23.667 --> 00:40:24.933
KATH, I WAS KIDDING.

873
00:40:27.404 --> 00:40:29.304
OH, COME ON.

874
00:40:31.408 --> 00:40:32.540
HEY...

875
00:40:32.675 --> 00:40:34.275
I LOST A COUPLE
OF YOUR SOCKS, OKAY,


876
00:40:34.410 --> 00:40:35.543
AND DON'T ASK ME
WHERE THEY ARE


877
00:40:35.612 --> 00:40:36.610
BECAUSE I DON'T KNOW,

878
00:40:36.680 --> 00:40:38.346
AND THE SHEETS
ARE PINK, TOO,


879
00:40:38.348 --> 00:40:39.346
AND IT'S NOT MY FAULT.

880
00:40:39.382 --> 00:40:40.949
JENNY TIPPENS' KID

881
00:40:41.084 --> 00:40:42.216
LEFT A POMEGRANATE
IN HIS POCKET--


882
00:40:42.218 --> 00:40:43.951
BABY, BABY,
IT WAS A JOKE.


883
00:40:44.020 --> 00:40:46.220
I WASN'T MAKING FUN OF YOU.

884
00:40:46.289 --> 00:40:48.155
I DON'T HAVE TIME FOR JOKES,
JOHN, OKAY?


885
00:40:48.191 --> 00:40:49.690
I'VE GOT SHEETS, AND SOCKS,

886
00:40:49.759 --> 00:40:51.892
AND QUARTERS THAT GO IN
UPSIDE DOWN.


887
00:40:51.928 --> 00:40:53.928
YOU'RE NOT THE ONLY ONE
WITH RESPONSIBILITIES.


888
00:41:08.044 --> 00:41:10.444
MY MOM CALLED
THIS MORNING.


889
00:41:10.480 --> 00:41:12.646
SHE LOVED
THE PICTURES WE SENT,


890
00:41:12.716 --> 00:41:14.782
SAID I LOOKED JUST LIKE ADAM
WHEN I WAS A BABY.


891
00:41:16.987 --> 00:41:20.822
ADAM'S WAY CUTER
THAN I EVER WAS.


892
00:41:31.001 --> 00:41:34.001
I NEED TO GO BACK NOW.

893
00:41:34.004 --> 00:41:35.202
YOU KNOW?

894
00:41:35.271 --> 00:41:36.404
PICTURES AREN'T ENOUGH.

895
00:41:38.074 --> 00:41:41.542
I ALREADY CALLED THE AIRLINE,

896
00:41:41.677 --> 00:41:44.011
AND ADAM AND I CAN LEAVE
THE DAY AFTER TOMORROW,


897
00:41:44.014 --> 00:41:46.147
BE BACK IN A WEEK.

898
00:41:46.216 --> 00:41:48.983
WOULD THAT BE OKAY?

899
00:41:50.353 --> 00:41:51.552
OF COURSE.

900
00:41:51.687 --> 00:41:54.288
I'LL FREEZE SOME FOOD

901
00:41:54.357 --> 00:41:55.422
AND I'LL MAKE SURE
ALL THE UTILITIES ARE PAID--


902
00:41:55.458 --> 00:41:56.690
KATH, HEY...

903
00:41:56.760 --> 00:42:00.161
GO TO BOISE AND STAY
AS LONG AS YOU WANT, OKAY?


904
00:42:00.230 --> 00:42:01.362
I'LL BE FINE.

905
00:42:02.899 --> 00:42:03.964
ARE YOU SURE?

906
00:42:04.000 --> 00:42:07.301
ABSOLUTELY.

907
00:42:07.337 --> 00:42:10.237
IT'LL GIVE ME TIME
TO LOOK FOR MY LOST SOCKS.


908
00:42:10.273 --> 00:42:13.040
HEY...

909
00:42:13.076 --> 00:42:14.641
NOW YOU ARE MAKING FUN OF ME.

910
00:42:14.677 --> 00:42:16.844
A LITTLE BIT, YEAH.

911
00:42:16.913 --> 00:42:19.113
[CHUCKLES]

912
00:42:19.115 --> 00:42:20.782
OKAY.

913
00:42:22.118 --> 00:42:25.086
GOOD NIGHT.

914
00:42:30.160 --> 00:42:31.259
GOOD NIGHT.

915
00:42:31.261 --> 00:42:33.227
GOOD NIGHT.

916
00:42:41.871 --> 00:42:43.237
THANKS.

917
00:42:45.475 --> 00:42:46.908
TAKE CARE.

918
00:42:49.779 --> 00:42:51.779
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

919
00:42:53.883 --> 00:42:57.084
YEAH, NOT A CHANCE.

920
00:42:57.120 --> 00:42:58.886
SHE LOOKED ME
IN THE EYES.


921
00:42:58.955 --> 00:43:00.955
DUDE...

922
00:43:01.090 --> 00:43:03.558
[HOCKEY GAME PLAYS
ON TELEVISION]


923
00:43:03.560 --> 00:43:05.359
<i>...THE SHOT, 
THE SAVE...</i>

924
00:43:05.395 --> 00:43:06.494
<i>REBOUND!</i>

925
00:43:06.563 --> 00:43:08.696
[CROWD SHOUTS AND CHEERS]

926
00:43:08.831 --> 00:43:11.232
[JAKE GROANS]

927
00:43:11.367 --> 00:43:13.834
OPEN NET,
AND HE PUSHES IT WIDE.


928
00:43:13.903 --> 00:43:15.770
IDIOT!

929
00:43:17.407 --> 00:43:18.573
YOU BORED?

930
00:43:19.976 --> 00:43:21.242
1-1 IN OVERTIME, YOU'RE BORED?

931
00:43:21.377 --> 00:43:23.444
IT'S VALENTINE'S DAY.

932
00:43:23.513 --> 00:43:24.711
I DON'T WANT TO MISS
KATH'S CALL.


933
00:43:24.747 --> 00:43:26.647
GIVE IT TO ME.

934
00:43:26.649 --> 00:43:27.515
- NO.
- GIVE IT.


935
00:43:27.650 --> 00:43:28.649
HEY, COME ON.

936
00:43:28.651 --> 00:43:31.419
GIVE IT TO ME,
OR JUST SOCK IT AWAY, MAN.


937
00:43:32.989 --> 00:43:34.721
LISTEN TO ME,

938
00:43:34.757 --> 00:43:37.458
YOU'RE ALLOWED
TO HAVE FUN, JOHN.


939
00:43:37.460 --> 00:43:38.993
GET DRUNK WITH ME,

940
00:43:39.128 --> 00:43:41.061
SING FIGHT SONGS.

941
00:43:41.131 --> 00:43:42.930
BE A FRESHMAN, MAN.

942
00:43:42.999 --> 00:43:44.265
[CROWD ERUPTS IN CHEERING]

943
00:43:44.267 --> 00:43:45.733
[CROWD ROARING]

944
00:43:45.802 --> 00:43:47.935
YES!

945
00:43:47.971 --> 00:43:49.403
DAMMIT.

946
00:43:49.439 --> 00:43:52.974
BIGGEST GOAL OF THE SEASON,
I WAS LOOKING THE OTHER WAY.


947
00:43:55.011 --> 00:43:56.610
YOU FORGET ABOUT
THAT PHONE CALL, MAN.


948
00:43:56.646 --> 00:43:57.811
I OWN YOU TONIGHT.

949
00:43:57.847 --> 00:43:59.213
WE GOT A STOP TO MAKE.

950
00:43:59.282 --> 00:44:01.149
COME ON.

951
00:44:03.052 --> 00:44:04.018
[TELEPHONE RINGING]

952
00:44:04.087 --> 00:44:05.953
DON'T HANG UP, I'M COMING!

953
00:44:05.989 --> 00:44:07.622
I'M COMING, KATHY, HANG ON!

954
00:44:07.624 --> 00:44:10.358
HANG ON, HANG ON, KATH...

955
00:44:10.493 --> 00:44:11.892
HELLO?

956
00:44:11.961 --> 00:44:13.293
HEY...

957
00:44:13.329 --> 00:44:15.829
HEY, KATH, HOW YOU DOING?

958
00:44:15.865 --> 00:44:17.698
NO, I'M SORRY, MY CELL DIED,

959
00:44:17.734 --> 00:44:20.434
AND THEN JAKE DRAGGED ME
TO A PARTY.


960
00:44:20.503 --> 00:44:22.369
KATH, THE BLUE BUNNY.

961
00:44:22.405 --> 00:44:23.437
NO, I'M LOOKING AT IT.

962
00:44:23.473 --> 00:44:26.640
YOU FORGOT IT, KATH.

963
00:44:26.676 --> 00:44:28.375
ADAM'S IN BOISE
WITHOUT HIS BLUE BUNNY,


964
00:44:28.411 --> 00:44:30.845
SO MAYBE YOU SHOULD
BRING HIM HOME


965
00:44:30.847 --> 00:44:34.982
SO HE WON'T BE SAD?

966
00:44:35.051 --> 00:44:37.251
YOU KNOW WHAT ELSE, KATH?

967
00:44:37.320 --> 00:44:40.054
I MISS YOU SO MUCH.

968
00:44:40.123 --> 00:44:41.522
OKAY, SO...

969
00:44:41.524 --> 00:44:43.591
COME HOME SOON?

970
00:44:43.726 --> 00:44:47.061
BRING MY FAMILY HOME, PLEASE.

971
00:45:04.080 --> 00:45:05.546
HEY, BUDDY.

972
00:45:05.615 --> 00:45:07.882
WELCOME HOME, ADAM.

973
00:45:09.919 --> 00:45:11.018
HEY, BUD...

974
00:45:24.167 --> 00:45:26.100
WELCOME HOME.

975
00:45:26.169 --> 00:45:27.235
WHY...

976
00:45:27.370 --> 00:45:28.769
WHY DID YOU
REARRANGE EVERYTHING?


977
00:45:28.838 --> 00:45:29.903
OH, JUST THE GLASSES.

978
00:45:29.939 --> 00:45:30.971
I THOUGHT THEY'D BE
EASIER TO REACH


979
00:45:31.007 --> 00:45:32.206
ON THE FIRST SHELF.

980
00:45:35.244 --> 00:45:36.444
I MISSED YOU.

981
00:45:40.716 --> 00:45:43.117
I'M GOING TO GO CHECK ON ADAM.

982
00:45:47.256 --> 00:45:49.257
[FUSSING AND CRYING]

983
00:45:53.429 --> 00:45:55.662
I GOT A B-PLUS
ON THAT ECON EXAM.


984
00:45:55.698 --> 00:45:57.598
THAT'S GREAT.

985
00:45:57.600 --> 00:45:59.666
HOW'S CALC?

986
00:45:59.702 --> 00:46:02.603
DID I MENTION THE B-PLUS
ON THE ECON EXAM?


987
00:46:02.738 --> 00:46:03.670
CALC'S CALC.

988
00:46:03.706 --> 00:46:05.472
I KNEW IT WOULD
BE TOUGH.


989
00:46:05.541 --> 00:46:08.476
HANG ON, BUD,
I'M COMING!


990
00:46:08.611 --> 00:46:10.111
HEY...

991
00:46:11.681 --> 00:46:15.116
[BABY CALMS AND STOPS CRYING]

992
00:46:18.821 --> 00:46:21.622
THERE YOU GO...

993
00:46:21.691 --> 00:46:23.691
HE ONLY DOES THAT FOR YOU.

994
00:46:25.528 --> 00:46:27.161
REALLY?

995
00:46:28.631 --> 00:46:29.664
YEAH.

996
00:46:33.603 --> 00:46:35.303
HOW WAS HE IN BOISE?

997
00:46:35.438 --> 00:46:36.503
DID HE BEHAVE HIMSELF?

998
00:46:36.539 --> 00:46:38.673
YEAH, HE WAS GREAT.

999
00:46:46.149 --> 00:46:49.083
[♪♪]

1000
00:46:55.325 --> 00:46:57.491
MS. KOWALSKI...

1001
00:46:59.062 --> 00:47:01.562
MS. JONES...

1002
00:47:03.199 --> 00:47:04.832
AND MR. PATTON...

1003
00:47:07.103 --> 00:47:09.069
MR. SCHWARTZ.

1004
00:47:09.105 --> 00:47:11.205
WOULD YOU PASS
THAT BACK, PLEASE?


1005
00:47:11.340 --> 00:47:13.340
MS. LUDWICK...

1006
00:47:13.376 --> 00:47:14.608
WOULD YOU
PASS THAT BACK?


1007
00:47:14.677 --> 00:47:17.811
MR. LEWIS...

1008
00:47:17.880 --> 00:47:21.682
MR. LEE...

1009
00:47:21.684 --> 00:47:24.819
MR. JARDINE.

1010
00:47:24.954 --> 00:47:26.019
[CRYING]

1011
00:47:26.055 --> 00:47:28.289
WE'RE ALMOST DONE,
ALMOST DONE, COME ON.


1012
00:47:28.424 --> 00:47:31.158
SHH, SHH, SHH, SHH...

1013
00:47:31.160 --> 00:47:34.094
[BABY CRYING]

1014
00:47:34.097 --> 00:47:37.698
BABY, STOP.

1015
00:47:37.700 --> 00:47:39.232
WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?

1016
00:47:39.268 --> 00:47:40.300
YOU WERE SUPPOSED TO
BE HERE AN HOUR AGO.


1017
00:47:40.336 --> 00:47:41.635
I NEED TO GO
TO THE STORE.


1018
00:47:41.771 --> 00:47:42.903
I HAD TO SEE
PROFESSOR KOWAL.


1019
00:47:42.972 --> 00:47:44.371
SHH, SHH, SHH, SHH...

1020
00:47:44.440 --> 00:47:45.505
WHAT'S THE MATTER,

1021
00:47:45.541 --> 00:47:46.774
YOU TOUCH
HIS HEAD AGAIN?


1022
00:47:46.776 --> 00:47:48.242
WE'RE FINE.

1023
00:47:48.244 --> 00:47:49.577
[BABY STILL CRYING
INCONSOLABLY]


1024
00:47:49.579 --> 00:47:51.712
LET ME GET HIM.

1025
00:47:51.714 --> 00:47:53.513
HEY, BIG GUY.

1026
00:47:53.549 --> 00:47:56.183
SHH, HEY, IT'S OKAY.

1027
00:47:57.920 --> 00:47:59.386
SHH...

1028
00:47:59.422 --> 00:48:01.855
THERE YOU GO, THERE YOU GO...

1029
00:48:01.924 --> 00:48:03.924
[BABY CALMS]

1030
00:48:03.960 --> 00:48:05.626
HOW DID YOU DO THAT?

1031
00:48:07.296 --> 00:48:08.462
HE'S ALWAYS HAPPY
WITH YOU.


1032
00:48:08.597 --> 00:48:09.597
HE'S ALWAYS SMILING.

1033
00:48:09.599 --> 00:48:11.198
EVERY TIME I TOUCH HIM,
HE-HE SCREAMS.


1034
00:48:11.267 --> 00:48:12.933
THAT'S NOT TRUE,
KATH.


1035
00:48:12.935 --> 00:48:14.668
YES, IT IS, JOHN,
YOU WEREN'T IN BOISE.


1036
00:48:14.670 --> 00:48:15.736
HE WAS SCREAMING
EVERY TWO SECONDS.


1037
00:48:15.805 --> 00:48:17.537
EVERYONE WAS LOOKING AT ME.
IT WAS EMBARRASSING.


1038
00:48:17.573 --> 00:48:19.673
HE WAS PROBABLY JUST TIRED.

1039
00:48:19.809 --> 00:48:22.176
NO, HE WASN'T TIRED.

1040
00:48:23.412 --> 00:48:24.411
HE HATES ME.

1041
00:48:24.414 --> 00:48:26.414
KATH, DON'T...

1042
00:48:31.053 --> 00:48:32.286
OKAY, BUDDY.

1043
00:48:48.371 --> 00:48:50.805
ARE YOU AWAKE?

1044
00:50:07.583 --> 00:50:09.850
HEY, I'M HOME.

1045
00:50:13.656 --> 00:50:17.525
HEY, WHAT
ARE YOU DOING?


1046
00:50:17.660 --> 00:50:19.193
I'M LEAVING.

1047
00:50:19.195 --> 00:50:20.260
YOU'RE...

1048
00:50:20.263 --> 00:50:23.597
W-WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
YOU'RE LEAVING?


1049
00:50:23.666 --> 00:50:25.131
THIS MAKES NO SENSE.

1050
00:50:25.167 --> 00:50:27.268
IT MAKES PERFECT
SENSE, OKAY?


1051
00:50:27.403 --> 00:50:28.936
HE'S NOT HAPPY
BECAUSE I'M NOT HAPPY.


1052
00:50:28.938 --> 00:50:30.404
I'M THE PROBLEM.

1053
00:50:30.406 --> 00:50:31.605
WHAT PROBLEM?

1054
00:50:31.607 --> 00:50:32.673
THERE'S NO PROBLEM.

1055
00:50:32.675 --> 00:50:35.209
WHY DON'T YOU SIT AT HOME
ALL DAY, EVERY DAY,


1056
00:50:35.211 --> 00:50:36.543
AND SEE IF YOU STILL THINK THAT.

1057
00:50:36.612 --> 00:50:37.611
KATH, DON'T DO--

1058
00:50:37.680 --> 00:50:39.346
DON'T DO THIS.

1059
00:50:39.348 --> 00:50:40.414
I'VE GOT TO GO
PICK UP ADAM--


1060
00:50:40.483 --> 00:50:41.482
NO, LEAVE HIM AT BEV'S.

1061
00:50:41.484 --> 00:50:43.017
HEY...

1062
00:50:43.152 --> 00:50:45.419
WHATEVER IT IS,
WE'LL FIX IT.


1063
00:50:45.554 --> 00:50:48.022
YOU CAN'T FIX A BABY!

1064
00:50:49.792 --> 00:50:50.890
YOU DON'T KNOW WHAT IT'S LIKE.

1065
00:50:50.927 --> 00:50:51.958
ALL I DO IS WAIT
FOR YOU TO GET HOME.


1066
00:50:51.994 --> 00:50:52.960
I HAVE YOUR SCHEDULE
MEMORIZED


1067
00:50:53.029 --> 00:50:54.094
SO I KNOW EXACTLY

1068
00:50:54.130 --> 00:50:55.295
WHEN YOU'RE GOING TO
WALK THROUGH THE DOOR,


1069
00:50:55.331 --> 00:50:56.563
'CAUSE THAT'S WHEN
MY LIFE BEGINS.


1070
00:50:56.632 --> 00:50:58.499
IT'S THE FIRST TIME
I GET TO SEE MY KID SMILE.


1071
00:50:58.634 --> 00:51:00.701
THAT'S CRAZY.
ADAM LOVES YOU.


1072
00:51:02.371 --> 00:51:03.304
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

1073
00:51:03.439 --> 00:51:04.571
HAVE I LET YOU DOWN
SOMEHOW?


1074
00:51:04.640 --> 00:51:06.306
- NO, OF COURSE NOT.
- DON'T YOU TRUST ME?


1075
00:51:06.309 --> 00:51:07.641
IT'S NOT ABOUT TRUST!

1076
00:51:07.643 --> 00:51:09.042
WHAT, THEN?

1077
00:51:09.078 --> 00:51:11.579
KATH, ANSWER ME.

1078
00:51:24.927 --> 00:51:26.794
[QUIETLY]: I TRAPPED YOU.

1079
00:51:28.331 --> 00:51:29.463
WHAT?

1080
00:51:31.601 --> 00:51:34.067
I GOT PREGNANT
ON PURPOSE, OKAY?


1081
00:51:34.136 --> 00:51:36.670
I TRAPPED YOU.

1082
00:51:36.706 --> 00:51:37.738
I DON'T BELIEVE THAT.

1083
00:51:37.873 --> 00:51:41.342
WELL, IT'S TRUE.

1084
00:51:41.477 --> 00:51:43.444
I KNEW YOU'D DO THE RIGHT THING
AND MARRY ME.


1085
00:51:45.781 --> 00:51:47.414
HOW DO YOU KNOW
IT WASN'T MY IDEA


1086
00:51:47.416 --> 00:51:48.482
TO GET YOU PREGNANT?

1087
00:51:50.686 --> 00:51:53.086
I WAS SCARED OF LEAVING BOISE,

1088
00:51:53.122 --> 00:51:55.956
SCARED OF LOSING YOU.

1089
00:51:55.958 --> 00:51:57.757
MAYBE I GOT YOU PREGNANT
TO KEEP US TOGETHER.


1090
00:51:57.793 --> 00:52:01.295
SEE?

1091
00:52:01.297 --> 00:52:02.562
I CAN ALWAYS COUNT ON YOU

1092
00:52:02.598 --> 00:52:04.031
TO SAY SOMETHING
AMAZING LIKE THAT,


1093
00:52:04.166 --> 00:52:05.766
JUST LIKE I COULD COUNT ON YOU
TO MARRY ME.


1094
00:52:05.901 --> 00:52:08.035
KATH, NONE OF THIS MATTERS.

1095
00:52:08.170 --> 00:52:10.037
HOWEVER WE GOT HERE,
WE'RE A FAMILY NOW--


1096
00:52:10.172 --> 00:52:11.371
NO!

1097
00:52:11.407 --> 00:52:12.639
YOU AND ADAM
ARE A FAMILY.


1098
00:52:12.708 --> 00:52:13.907
I'M JUST THE GIRL
WHO PUTS THE GLASSES


1099
00:52:14.043 --> 00:52:15.042
ON THE WRONG SHELF!

1100
00:52:15.044 --> 00:52:16.843
WHAT DOES THAT EVEN MEAN?

1101
00:52:16.879 --> 00:52:20.046
YOU EARNED HARVARD, OKAY?

1102
00:52:20.082 --> 00:52:21.448
I
-I DON'T BELONG HERE.

1103
00:52:21.517 --> 00:52:23.583
I SCHEMED MY WAY IN!

1104
00:52:23.653 --> 00:52:24.585
HERE'S AN IDEA.

1105
00:52:24.720 --> 00:52:26.787
WHY DON'T YOU STOP
THINKING ABOUT YOURSELF?


1106
00:52:26.856 --> 00:52:28.455
THAT'S NOT FAIR!

1107
00:52:28.590 --> 00:52:30.657
AND RUNNING AWAY IS?

1108
00:52:30.726 --> 00:52:32.393
I'M NOT RUNNING AWAY,
I'M GOING HOME!


1109
00:52:35.331 --> 00:52:39.066
I THOUGHT MY DREAMS WERE
THE SAME AS YOURS, BUT...


1110
00:52:39.135 --> 00:52:41.668
THEY'RE NOT.

1111
00:52:41.704 --> 00:52:44.538
I MADE A HUGE MISTAKE, JOHN.

1112
00:52:47.543 --> 00:52:50.611
MAYBE THAT'S SELFISH.

1113
00:52:50.746 --> 00:52:53.012
I DON'T CARE ANYMORE.

1114
00:52:53.049 --> 00:52:54.214
I CAN'T PRETEND.

1115
00:52:54.250 --> 00:52:56.884
THAT'S YOUR DREAM, HUH?

1116
00:52:57.019 --> 00:52:59.753
TO TAKE AWAY MY SON?

1117
00:52:59.755 --> 00:53:01.621
TO BREAK MY HEART,
THAT'S YOUR DREAM?


1118
00:53:01.691 --> 00:53:04.357
NO.

1119
00:53:04.393 --> 00:53:05.693
OF COURSE NOT.

1120
00:53:11.767 --> 00:53:15.635
I'M GOING HOME, JOHN.

1121
00:53:15.705 --> 00:53:17.905
OKAY?

1122
00:53:17.907 --> 00:53:19.840
AND I'M LEAVING ADAM WITH YOU.

1123
00:53:22.845 --> 00:53:23.844
NO...

1124
00:53:23.979 --> 00:53:27.214
I'M SORRY.

1125
00:54:38.788 --> 00:54:42.656
THERE'S NO MOON
TONIGHT.


1126
00:54:42.725 --> 00:54:45.325
IT'S LOWER
IN THE SKY.


1127
00:54:45.394 --> 00:54:48.128
YOU WEREN'T LOOKING
HARD ENOUGH.


1128
00:54:59.675 --> 00:55:02.142
DO YOU REALLY WANT TO KNOW
WHY I'M GOING BACK?


1129
00:55:04.280 --> 00:55:06.713
I THINK I DESERVE THAT.

1130
00:55:10.486 --> 00:55:12.152
IT WAS ADAM'S BLUE BUNNY.

1131
00:55:14.890 --> 00:55:16.890
I FOUND IT IN BED TODAY,

1132
00:55:17.025 --> 00:55:20.294
AND IT WAS LIKE
THIS GIANT REVELATION,


1133
00:55:20.296 --> 00:55:24.364
LIKE A BOMB WENT OFF IN MY HEAD.

1134
00:55:24.499 --> 00:55:26.433
YOU SLEPT WITH
OUR SON'S FAVORITE TOY,


1135
00:55:26.502 --> 00:55:29.169
AND I DIDN'T EVEN REMEMBER
TO PACK IT.


1136
00:55:31.840 --> 00:55:34.141
ONE OF US
JUST ISN'T A PARENT, JOHN.


1137
00:55:36.511 --> 00:55:38.311
ONE OF US IS STILL A PROM QUEEN.

1138
00:55:38.380 --> 00:55:40.113
KATH, THAT'S NOT TRUE.

1139
00:55:40.149 --> 00:55:41.180
YOU'RE A GREAT MOM--

1140
00:55:41.217 --> 00:55:42.449
NO.

1141
00:55:42.518 --> 00:55:45.319
YOU DON'T HAVE TO DEFEND ME.

1142
00:55:45.454 --> 00:55:46.520
I KNOW THE TRUTH.

1143
00:55:46.655 --> 00:55:48.255
I'VE GROWN UP THAT MUCH.

1144
00:55:55.464 --> 00:55:57.097
I WANT TO GO HOME.

1145
00:55:59.501 --> 00:56:03.270
I MISS MY CROWN.

1146
00:56:05.941 --> 00:56:08.608
AND IT'S ONLY IN BOISE?

1147
00:56:08.611 --> 00:56:10.611
YOU'RE ABSOLUTELY SURE?

1148
00:56:13.615 --> 00:56:16.416
BEDROOM CLOSET,

1149
00:56:16.551 --> 00:56:18.017
SECOND SHELF,

1150
00:56:18.053 --> 00:56:19.620
RIGHT BEHIND MY POM
-POMS.

1151
00:56:53.155 --> 00:56:56.056
OKAY, JUST...

1152
00:56:56.191 --> 00:56:58.658
MAKE SURE YOU SERVE HIM
HIS CEREAL WARM, OKAY?


1153
00:56:58.727 --> 00:57:00.927
OH, AND YOU CAN
GET HIM THOSE...


1154
00:57:00.930 --> 00:57:02.462
THOSE EXTRA
-SOFT UNDERSHIRTS

1155
00:57:02.597 --> 00:57:05.198
AT, UM...

1156
00:57:05.267 --> 00:57:07.000
GOD...

1157
00:57:07.135 --> 00:57:09.869
I CAN'T REMEMBER
THE NAME OF THE STORE.


1158
00:57:09.939 --> 00:57:12.072
THE LIST, KATHY,
IT'S ON THE LIST.


1159
00:57:12.207 --> 00:57:13.407
RIGHT.

1160
00:57:13.542 --> 00:57:14.741
RIGHT, RIGHT, RIGHT, THE LIST.

1161
00:57:14.777 --> 00:57:16.944
CEREAL WARM, UNDERSHIRTS SOFT,
GOT IT.


1162
00:57:19.548 --> 00:57:21.081
LADY,
IT'S TIME TO GO.


1163
00:57:26.522 --> 00:57:28.121
HERE.

1164
00:57:39.301 --> 00:57:41.301
SEE HOW HE LOVES YOU?

1165
00:57:45.708 --> 00:57:47.808
STAY.

1166
00:57:50.245 --> 00:57:52.779
PLEASE STAY.

1167
00:58:01.590 --> 00:58:05.559
[BABY CRYING]

1168
00:58:20.675 --> 00:58:23.143
YOU AND ME, BUDDY...

1169
00:58:25.480 --> 00:58:27.881
RIGHT TO THE END.

1170
00:58:29.818 --> 00:58:32.085
I'M NOT GOING TO
LIE TO YOU.


1171
00:58:32.154 --> 00:58:35.621
I'M SCARED.

1172
00:58:35.657 --> 00:58:38.758
IT'S JUST US GUYS NOW,

1173
00:58:38.761 --> 00:58:40.894
AND WE GOT TO STICK TOGETHER

1174
00:58:40.896 --> 00:58:43.029
AND WATCH EACH OTHER'S BACKS.

1175
00:58:43.098 --> 00:58:44.764
BE A REAL FAMILY.

1176
00:58:44.833 --> 00:58:47.768
I'M HOPING I CAN COUNT ON
YOUR COMPLETE COOPERATION.


1177
00:58:47.903 --> 00:58:49.369
ARE YOU ON BOARD?

1178
00:58:52.241 --> 00:58:56.410
I'LL TAKE THAT AS A YES.

1179
00:59:34.249 --> 00:59:35.882
SHE LEFT YOU?

1180
00:59:35.884 --> 00:59:37.016
SHE WAS HOMESICK.

1181
00:59:37.052 --> 00:59:37.950
AND YOUR SON?

1182
00:59:37.986 --> 00:59:38.885
WITH ME.

1183
00:59:39.020 --> 00:59:42.289
OH, MY.

1184
00:59:42.291 --> 00:59:43.223
IT'S OKAY, WE'RE MANAGING.

1185
00:59:43.292 --> 00:59:46.293
NOT IN CALCULUS, I'M AFRAID.

1186
00:59:47.829 --> 00:59:49.162
I'M GOING TO GIVE
YOU THE NUMBER


1187
00:59:49.297 --> 00:59:50.497
OF A GRAD STUDENT.

1188
00:59:50.632 --> 00:59:51.832
HE'S A TUTOR,

1189
00:59:51.967 --> 00:59:53.966
AND HE KNOWS
THE MATERIAL VERY WELL.


1190
00:59:54.002 --> 00:59:55.302
SIR, I...

1191
00:59:55.437 --> 00:59:56.369
I CAN'T AFFORD A TUTOR.

1192
00:59:56.405 --> 00:59:57.304
NOT TO WORRY.

1193
00:59:57.439 --> 00:59:58.572
LAST TIME I CHECKED,

1194
00:59:58.574 --> 01:00:01.307
HARVARD'S ENDOWMENT
WAS ALMOST 26 BILLION.


1195
01:00:01.343 --> 01:00:03.776
I THINK THAT'LL
COVER IT.


1196
01:00:03.846 --> 01:00:06.246
I'LL EXPECT
REPAYMENT, OF COURSE...


1197
01:00:06.381 --> 01:00:07.714
A PASSING GRADE.

1198
01:00:07.849 --> 01:00:10.317
ABSOLUTELY.

1199
01:00:12.154 --> 01:00:14.454
THANK YOU,
PROFESSOR KOWAL.


1200
01:00:14.523 --> 01:00:16.456
I'LL DELIVER,
I PROMISE.


1201
01:00:16.525 --> 01:00:18.125
I'M AFRAID
YOU'LL HAVE TO, JOHN.


1202
01:00:18.260 --> 01:00:20.861
THE ALTERNATIVE
IS GRIM.


1203
01:00:27.202 --> 01:00:30.203
HEY, HOW'D IT GO?

1204
01:00:30.272 --> 01:00:33.006
OOH!
SHH, SHH, SHH...


1205
01:00:34.309 --> 01:00:35.675
YOU MUST HAVE
MAGICAL POWERS.


1206
01:00:35.677 --> 01:00:37.611
HE NEVER NAPS
IN THE AFTERNOON.


1207
01:00:37.746 --> 01:00:40.012
OH, IT WASN'T ME,
IT WAS THE SONG.


1208
01:00:40.048 --> 01:00:41.147
"WHEELS ON THE BUS."

1209
01:00:41.216 --> 01:00:42.816
ONE CHORUS,
AND IT WAS DREAMLAND.


1210
01:00:42.951 --> 01:00:44.217
I'VE NEVER SEEN
ANYTHING LIKE IT.


1211
01:00:44.286 --> 01:00:46.419
"THE WHEELS ON THE BUS"?

1212
01:00:46.455 --> 01:00:49.222
NOW OFFICIALLY
MY FAVORITE SONG.


1213
01:00:49.357 --> 01:00:51.458
[CHUCKLES QUIETLY]

1214
01:00:57.899 --> 01:00:59.799
THANKS, BEV.

1215
01:01:08.610 --> 01:01:10.042
YOU'RE NOT
THE FIRST STUDENT


1216
01:01:10.078 --> 01:01:11.845
THAT KOWAL'S
SENT TO SEE ME.


1217
01:01:11.847 --> 01:01:13.713
EVERYTHING MAKES SENSE
WHEN I'M HERE WITH YOU,


1218
01:01:13.715 --> 01:01:16.182
BUT PROFESSOR KOWAL
PUTS IT IN A TEST,


1219
01:01:16.218 --> 01:01:17.317
I BLANK.

1220
01:01:17.386 --> 01:01:19.319
YOU KNOW, I'M FINE

1221
01:01:19.321 --> 01:01:20.920
IN ALL MY OTHER COURSES, TOO.

1222
01:01:20.923 --> 01:01:23.189
I'M EVEN ACING ECON.

1223
01:01:23.192 --> 01:01:25.358
IT'S DRIVING ME NUTS.

1224
01:01:26.995 --> 01:01:27.927
WE ALL FALL SHORT
SOMEWHERE.


1225
01:01:27.963 --> 01:01:29.528
CALC BULLIES ME.

1226
01:01:29.565 --> 01:01:31.331
YOU KNOW, I SEE IT COMING,

1227
01:01:31.333 --> 01:01:33.733
AND I GET CLAMMY AND WEAK.

1228
01:01:33.735 --> 01:01:35.001
IT'S LIKE...

1229
01:01:35.037 --> 01:01:36.102
IT'S LIKE KRYPTONITE.

1230
01:01:37.939 --> 01:01:39.873
OKAY, SUPERMAN,

1231
01:01:39.875 --> 01:01:43.176
TRY NUMBER 16.

1232
01:01:44.780 --> 01:01:47.013
ALL RIGHT.

1233
01:02:17.379 --> 01:02:20.447
[BABY FUSSING AND COOING]

1234
01:02:21.750 --> 01:02:24.517
REASON #63 WHY WE MISS MOMMY--

1235
01:02:24.653 --> 01:02:28.988
NO CLEAN CLOTHES.

1236
01:02:29.057 --> 01:02:31.725
HEY, YOUR UNCLE JAKE'S
GOING TO BABYSIT YOU TODAY.


1237
01:02:31.860 --> 01:02:33.093
DADDY'S GOT A BIG TEST.

1238
01:02:34.129 --> 01:02:35.061
I KNOW, BUD,
I KNOW.


1239
01:02:35.097 --> 01:02:36.462
IT'S--

1240
01:02:36.531 --> 01:02:37.530
AH!

1241
01:02:37.532 --> 01:02:39.099
DAMMIT...

1242
01:02:43.204 --> 01:02:44.871
THUMBTACK.

1243
01:02:44.873 --> 01:02:45.905
REASON #64.

1244
01:02:48.810 --> 01:02:49.876
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

1245
01:02:50.011 --> 01:02:51.111
THANK GOD.

1246
01:02:54.750 --> 01:02:56.349
AH, HEY, JOHN,
IS THIS A GOOD TIME?


1247
01:02:56.351 --> 01:02:58.752
I-I WAS JUST GOING OUT,
ACTUALLY.


1248
01:02:58.754 --> 01:03:00.686
YOU KNOW WHAT?

1249
01:03:00.722 --> 01:03:03.622
WE CAN COME BACK LATER,
WHENEVER'S CONVENIENT.


1250
01:03:03.659 --> 01:03:05.325
CONVENIENT FOR WHAT?

1251
01:03:07.095 --> 01:03:08.161
TO SHOW THE PLACE.

1252
01:03:10.298 --> 01:03:11.798
I'M SORRY, JOHN,
YOU GOT THE NOTICE, DIDN'T YOU?


1253
01:03:13.101 --> 01:03:15.702
NO, TIM, I DIDN'T.

1254
01:03:15.704 --> 01:03:17.770
I CAN'T AUTHORIZE
MARRIED HOUSING


1255
01:03:17.806 --> 01:03:18.771
FOR A SINGLE MAN.

1256
01:03:18.840 --> 01:03:20.373
THE RULES ARE
VERY CLEAR.


1257
01:03:20.442 --> 01:03:22.108
WHAT ABOUT
FAMILY HOUSING?


1258
01:03:22.110 --> 01:03:23.243
ADAM AND I
ARE A FAMILY.


1259
01:03:23.378 --> 01:03:24.311
THE RULES STIPULATE--

1260
01:03:24.446 --> 01:03:25.378
BREAK THE RULES.

1261
01:03:25.414 --> 01:03:26.713
JOHN, YOU'RE NOT
HEARING ME OUT.


1262
01:03:26.848 --> 01:03:28.314
YOU HAVE OPTIONS.

1263
01:03:28.350 --> 01:03:29.716
I CAN RELEASE
THE SCHOLARSHIP FUNDS


1264
01:03:29.718 --> 01:03:30.784
THAT GO TO
MARRIED HOUSING,


1265
01:03:30.786 --> 01:03:32.185
AND YOU CAN FIND
AN APARTMENT.


1266
01:03:32.320 --> 01:03:33.586
I CAN'T FIND
A CLEAN SHIRT.


1267
01:03:33.655 --> 01:03:34.788
THAT'S WHY I DIDN'T
GET YOUR NOTICE.


1268
01:03:34.790 --> 01:03:35.922
I DON'T HAVE TIME
TO CHECK MY MAILBOX.


1269
01:03:36.057 --> 01:03:36.989
YOU'RE OVERWHELMED.

1270
01:03:37.025 --> 01:03:38.124
I'M RAISING
A CHILD!


1271
01:03:38.193 --> 01:03:39.459
AND MAYBE
FLUNKING OUT.


1272
01:03:39.461 --> 01:03:41.795
THE LAST TIME
WE TALKED,


1273
01:03:41.930 --> 01:03:44.064
YOU HAD A WIFE
TO TAKE CARE OF YOUR BABY.


1274
01:03:44.199 --> 01:03:46.266
NOW YOU'RE A SINGLE FATHER.

1275
01:03:46.268 --> 01:03:47.467
THE STAKES ARE HIGHER,

1276
01:03:47.536 --> 01:03:50.003
AND THE RULES
HAVE CHANGED.


1277
01:03:50.005 --> 01:03:51.404
IT'S NOT ABOUT RULES,

1278
01:03:51.539 --> 01:03:52.872
IT'S YOU.

1279
01:03:52.908 --> 01:03:54.541
YOU JUST PLAIN DON'T LIKE ME.

1280
01:03:54.543 --> 01:03:55.608
THAT WAS CLEAR FROM THE START.

1281
01:03:55.677 --> 01:03:57.009
YOU THINK I'VE CHEATED
SOME OTHER DESERVING GUY


1282
01:03:57.045 --> 01:03:58.545
OUT OF HIS HARVARD SHOT.

1283
01:03:58.547 --> 01:04:01.614
I THINK YOU HAVE A CHILD,

1284
01:04:01.683 --> 01:04:03.149
AND CHILDREN SHOULD COME FIRST.

1285
01:04:03.185 --> 01:04:06.352
MY SON IS MY LIFE.

1286
01:04:06.388 --> 01:04:07.587
I WON'T FAIL HIM...

1287
01:04:09.691 --> 01:04:11.957
AND I WON'T FAIL CALCULUS.

1288
01:04:11.993 --> 01:04:13.159
I BELONG HERE.

1289
01:04:13.294 --> 01:04:14.961
I MAY BE A BUMPKIN FROM BOISE,

1290
01:04:14.963 --> 01:04:16.763
BUT I EARNED HARVARD
AS MUCH AS YOU DID,


1291
01:04:16.898 --> 01:04:18.230
AND I WON'T
WALK AWAY FROM IT


1292
01:04:18.266 --> 01:04:20.233
JUST TO ACCOMMODATE
YOUR NARROW STANDARDS.


1293
01:04:21.570 --> 01:04:24.037
I TOLD YOU ONCE BEFORE,
I LEAVE ON MY OWN TERMS,


1294
01:04:24.039 --> 01:04:25.171
AND WHEN I DO,

1295
01:04:25.306 --> 01:04:27.674
I'M TAKING A HARVARD
DIPLOMA WITH ME.


1296
01:04:33.047 --> 01:04:34.914
NO, WE'RE DOING JUST FINE.
ADAM'S GREAT.


1297
01:04:34.950 --> 01:04:36.515
PLUS MY FRIEND JAKE'S
HELPING OUT


1298
01:04:36.551 --> 01:04:38.651
WITH BABY
-SITTING, SO...

1299
01:04:38.687 --> 01:04:41.521
SO WHEN'S KATH DUE BACK,
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA?


1300
01:04:41.590 --> 01:04:42.922
NO, NO, NOTHING IMPORTANT,

1301
01:04:42.958 --> 01:04:46.325
JUST, YOU KNOW, CHECKING IN.

1302
01:04:46.395 --> 01:04:49.195
TELL HER I CALLED, OKAY?

1303
01:04:49.330 --> 01:04:52.064
AND TELL HER...

1304
01:04:52.134 --> 01:04:55.935
TELL HER WE MISS HER.

1305
01:04:55.937 --> 01:04:59.873
YEAH, OKAY. BYE.

1306
01:05:02.277 --> 01:05:05.979
[BABY'S CRIES COME OVER MONITOR]

1307
01:05:11.887 --> 01:05:15.321
[♪♪]

1308
01:05:21.362 --> 01:05:23.530
ALL RIGHT.

1309
01:05:27.635 --> 01:05:28.701
<i>YEAH.</i>

1310
01:05:28.737 --> 01:05:30.437
HI. YEAH, I'D LIKE TO SEE
THE APARTMENT, PLEASE?


1311
01:05:30.572 --> 01:05:32.906
<i>IT WAS RENTED
YESTERDAY.</i>


1312
01:05:32.908 --> 01:05:33.906
[BABY FUSSING AND CRYING]

1313
01:05:33.942 --> 01:05:34.974
I KNOW, BUD.

1314
01:05:36.044 --> 01:05:38.845
IT DOESN'T MATTER WHERE WE ARE,
AS LONG AS WE'RE TOGETHER.


1315
01:05:40.782 --> 01:05:43.182
JUST REMEMBER, 
CHANGE IS GOOD.

1316
01:05:43.185 --> 01:05:44.918
YOU KNOW, IT BUILDS CHARACTER.

1317
01:05:44.920 --> 01:05:48.320
IT MAKES MEN.

1318
01:05:48.356 --> 01:05:50.123
[GROANS]

1319
01:05:50.125 --> 01:05:52.859
[SIGHS HEAVILY]

1320
01:05:52.994 --> 01:05:54.194
BOISE OR BOSTON,

1321
01:05:54.329 --> 01:05:55.995
WE'RE A TEAM.

1322
01:05:55.997 --> 01:05:58.198
THAT'S ONE THING
THAT'S NEVER GOING TO CHANGE.


1323
01:06:01.069 --> 01:06:03.002
NEED A LITTLE HELP
HERE, BUDDY.


1324
01:06:03.038 --> 01:06:04.203
DADDY'S STARTING TO GET WORRIED.

1325
01:06:04.239 --> 01:06:05.271
[RINGS DOORBELL]

1326
01:06:05.406 --> 01:06:06.739
[DOG BARKING]

1327
01:06:06.775 --> 01:06:08.007
[BABY CRIES]

1328
01:06:08.009 --> 01:06:10.342
IT'S OKAY.
IT'S OKAY, BUD.


1329
01:06:10.378 --> 01:06:12.145
[DOG BARKING]

1330
01:06:18.687 --> 01:06:22.522
WELL, IT'S ALWAYS DARKEST
BEFORE THE DAWN.


1331
01:06:36.104 --> 01:06:38.071
[RINGS DOORBELL]

1332
01:06:41.176 --> 01:06:42.775
HELLO!

1333
01:06:42.811 --> 01:06:45.111
HI, UH,
I SAW YOUR SIGN OUT FRONT.


1334
01:06:45.180 --> 01:06:47.246
OH, YEAH, I NEVER ADVERTISE
IN THE PAPER.


1335
01:06:47.315 --> 01:06:48.914
I DECIDE TO SEE
WHAT THE WIND BLOWS IN.


1336
01:06:48.950 --> 01:06:50.683
[BABY COOS]

1337
01:06:50.685 --> 01:06:51.718
WOULD YOU LIKE TO SEE THE ROOM?

1338
01:06:51.853 --> 01:06:52.919
YES, PLEASE.

1339
01:06:53.054 --> 01:06:54.320
[BABY FUSSES AND GURGLES]

1340
01:06:54.389 --> 01:06:55.455
COME ON IN.

1341
01:06:55.590 --> 01:06:56.990
THANK YOU.

1342
01:06:56.992 --> 01:06:58.858
HELLO, PRECIOUS.

1343
01:06:58.860 --> 01:07:01.928
OH, YES, THERE'S
PLENTY OF ROOM FOR TWO.


1344
01:07:01.997 --> 01:07:03.663
IT'S 340 SQUARE FEET.

1345
01:07:03.732 --> 01:07:05.932
IT'S VERY BRIGHT, AND COZY, TOO.

1346
01:07:06.001 --> 01:07:07.533
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

1347
01:07:07.602 --> 01:07:09.201
UH, IT'S...

1348
01:07:09.237 --> 01:07:10.336
IT'S AMAZING.

1349
01:07:10.405 --> 01:07:11.938
YOU HAVE YOUR OWN
BATHROOM THERE,


1350
01:07:11.940 --> 01:07:13.406
AND KITCHEN PRIVILEGES

1351
01:07:13.475 --> 01:07:17.343
AND A WONDERFUL,
WONDERFUL BACKYARD.


1352
01:07:17.379 --> 01:07:20.079
YES...

1353
01:07:20.081 --> 01:07:21.747
I'M AFRAID TO ASK.
HOW MUCH?


1354
01:07:21.783 --> 01:07:24.083
FIRST, LAST,
AND SECURITY, $2000.


1355
01:07:26.187 --> 01:07:27.286
TOO MUCH?

1356
01:07:27.289 --> 01:07:30.156
UNFORTUNATELY, YEAH.

1357
01:07:30.291 --> 01:07:32.759
OH, MY GOODNESS.

1358
01:07:32.761 --> 01:07:34.293
YOUR AURA JUST WENT
FROM BLUE TO RED,


1359
01:07:34.329 --> 01:07:35.762
AND IT'S THROBBING
LIKE A TOOTHACHE.


1360
01:07:35.897 --> 01:07:38.431
[GASPING IN HORROR]

1361
01:07:38.567 --> 01:07:40.032
IT'S GOING TO GO BACK
TO PURPLE IN A SECOND.


1362
01:07:40.068 --> 01:07:41.033
YEAH, THERE IT IS.

1363
01:07:41.102 --> 01:07:42.769
[EXHALING IN RELIEF]

1364
01:07:42.771 --> 01:07:44.703
WHAT DO YOU SAY
I KNOCK IT DOWN TO $1,000?


1365
01:07:44.739 --> 01:07:46.973
I CAN'T HAVE THAT RED AURA
ON MY CONSCIENCE.


1366
01:07:47.108 --> 01:07:48.841
THAT KARMA WOULD SUCK.

1367
01:07:48.877 --> 01:07:50.577
SERIOUSLY?

1368
01:07:50.712 --> 01:07:51.644
YEAH.

1369
01:07:51.779 --> 01:07:54.581
[♪♪]

1370
01:07:54.716 --> 01:07:56.049
I DON'T GET IT.

1371
01:07:56.184 --> 01:07:58.250
HOW COME YOUR MOM CAN'T COME OUT
AND TAKE CARE OF ADAM?


1372
01:07:58.320 --> 01:07:59.919
SHE'S GOT
A FULL-TIME JOB,


1373
01:08:00.054 --> 01:08:02.388
PLUS I WOULD NEVER ASK HER.

1374
01:08:02.390 --> 01:08:03.589
I'VE BEEN
HERE 30 YEARS,


1375
01:08:03.592 --> 01:08:05.658
I DON'T HAVE
THIS MUCH STUFF.


1376
01:08:05.694 --> 01:08:07.660
TELL ME ABOUT IT.

1377
01:08:07.696 --> 01:08:08.728
LET'S GO SEE

1378
01:08:08.863 --> 01:08:11.130
WHERE THEY'RE GOING TO PUT
ALL THIS STUFF, BUDDY.


1379
01:08:11.265 --> 01:08:12.565
LET'S GO.

1380
01:08:16.871 --> 01:08:17.870
I GOT TO TELL YOU,

1381
01:08:17.939 --> 01:08:20.006
I DON'T REALLY
BUY INTO THIS STUFF.


1382
01:08:20.008 --> 01:08:22.609
WELL, "THIS STUFF"
BOUGHT THE VERY HOUSE


1383
01:08:22.744 --> 01:08:25.278
THAT YOU'RE LIVING IN.

1384
01:08:25.413 --> 01:08:26.546
[SHUFFLING CARDS]

1385
01:08:26.548 --> 01:08:29.182
OKAY, NOW...

1386
01:08:31.152 --> 01:08:32.819
FORTITUDE.

1387
01:08:32.821 --> 01:08:34.687
HMM...
IS THAT GOOD?


1388
01:08:34.756 --> 01:08:36.022
ONE OF THE BEST.

1389
01:08:36.091 --> 01:08:38.024
IT MEANS YOU HAVE RESILIENCE.

1390
01:08:38.026 --> 01:08:39.092
YOU'RE STRONG.

1391
01:08:39.094 --> 01:08:40.293
YOU ARE DETERMINED.

1392
01:08:40.295 --> 01:08:41.360
IF THAT'S A CALC. BOOK
HE'S CARRYING,


1393
01:08:41.363 --> 01:08:42.895
YOU'VE GOT YOURSELF A CONVERT.

1394
01:08:43.031 --> 01:08:44.464
SHH, SHH, SHH.

1395
01:08:46.167 --> 01:08:48.634
THE STAR.

1396
01:08:48.670 --> 01:08:49.635
SHE WHO GUIDES YOU.

1397
01:08:49.704 --> 01:08:50.703
MY MOTHER.

1398
01:08:52.107 --> 01:08:54.841
HARVARD WAS HER DREAM.

1399
01:08:54.843 --> 01:08:56.442
SHE BELIEVED IN ME
WHEN I DIDN'T.


1400
01:08:56.511 --> 01:08:58.844
THAT'S A MOTHER'S JOB.

1401
01:08:58.913 --> 01:09:00.046
UGH.

1402
01:09:00.048 --> 01:09:02.248
I HAVE BEEN MEANING
TO JUST THROW THIS ONE OUT.


1403
01:09:02.383 --> 01:09:03.249
EH, YOU KNOW...

1404
01:09:03.318 --> 01:09:05.785
FORTUNES,
THEY RISE, THEY FALL.


1405
01:09:05.854 --> 01:09:07.820
NEXT...

1406
01:09:09.190 --> 01:09:10.723
[WHISPERS DRAMATICALLY]:
DESIRE.


1407
01:09:12.527 --> 01:09:14.661
THIS IS A VERY POWERFUL CARD.

1408
01:09:14.762 --> 01:09:19.065
IN FOURTH POSITION,
IT GRANTS A WISH.


1409
01:09:21.403 --> 01:09:25.337
SO THINK VERY CAREFULLY
BEFORE YOU DECIDE.


1410
01:09:25.373 --> 01:09:27.874
IT MUST BE SOMETHING
THAT YOU WANT VERY MUCH.


1411
01:09:29.877 --> 01:09:31.811
TO BE A GOOD FATHER.

1412
01:09:31.880 --> 01:09:34.080
[LAUGHS]

1413
01:09:34.149 --> 01:09:36.548
YOU POOR MISGUIDED SOUL,

1414
01:09:36.584 --> 01:09:38.084
DO YOU REALIZE WHAT YOU'VE DONE?

1415
01:09:38.153 --> 01:09:39.485
YOU'VE BLOWN
A GUARANTEED PASS


1416
01:09:39.620 --> 01:09:40.987
IN CALCULUS.

1417
01:09:46.194 --> 01:09:49.028
YOU'VE WISHED FOR SOMETHING
THAT'S ALREADY COME TRUE.


1418
01:09:59.407 --> 01:10:00.707
WE HAVE A FRIDGE
FULL OF HOMEMADE SOUP


1419
01:10:00.842 --> 01:10:02.441
AND A FREE BABYSITTER
RIGHT DOWNSTAIRS.


1420
01:10:02.477 --> 01:10:03.576
[BABY COOS AND GURGLES]

1421
01:10:03.578 --> 01:10:04.977
HEY, YOU WANT TO SAY HI
TO ADAM?


1422
01:10:05.113 --> 01:10:06.379
SAY HI TO GRANDMA, BUD.

1423
01:10:13.722 --> 01:10:14.921
[KNOCKING URGENTLY]

1424
01:10:14.923 --> 01:10:16.923
NO, MA, I WOULDN'T LIE TO YOU.
I'M DOING JUST FINE.


1425
01:10:16.925 --> 01:10:18.524
LOOK, JAKE'S AT THE DOOR,
I GOTTA GO.


1426
01:10:18.593 --> 01:10:19.525
I'LL TALK
TO YOU LATER.


1427
01:10:19.660 --> 01:10:20.793
I LOVE YOU.

1428
01:10:20.795 --> 01:10:22.394
LATE AS USUAL.
I GOT A TEST TODAY.


1429
01:10:22.464 --> 01:10:23.462
YOU'RE NOT
PICKING UP YOUR PHONE?


1430
01:10:23.531 --> 01:10:24.663
I GOT AN EMERGENCY
AT WORK, MAN.


1431
01:10:24.733 --> 01:10:25.932
I CAN'T BABYSIT.

1432
01:10:26.067 --> 01:10:26.899
JAKE...

1433
01:10:26.901 --> 01:10:27.867
I CAN'T DO IT--

1434
01:10:27.936 --> 01:10:29.001
DOROTHY IS NOT AVAILABLE.

1435
01:10:29.037 --> 01:10:30.068
I'M SORRY.

1436
01:10:30.105 --> 01:10:31.204
I CAN'T--
I'M GOING TO GET YOU BACK.


1437
01:10:31.206 --> 01:10:32.271
WHAT AM I
GOING TO DO?


1438
01:10:32.273 --> 01:10:33.539
I'M SORRY.
I'M SORRY!


1439
01:10:33.674 --> 01:10:35.041
JAKE!

1440
01:10:40.014 --> 01:10:41.781
OH...

1441
01:10:55.696 --> 01:10:58.931
AGAIN, I'M SO
VERY, VERY SORRY.


1442
01:11:16.117 --> 01:11:18.851
[BABY STARTS FUSSING]

1443
01:11:20.588 --> 01:11:23.589
[WHISPERS]: OH, MY GOD.

1444
01:11:23.724 --> 01:11:24.657
HEY, SHH, SHH...
HEY, IT'S OKAY.


1445
01:11:24.792 --> 01:11:25.858
HEY, HEY,
HAPPY BOY.


1446
01:11:25.993 --> 01:11:27.326
HAPPY BOY, HAPPY BOY...

1447
01:11:27.362 --> 01:11:28.393
[BABY STARTS TO CRY]

1448
01:11:28.429 --> 01:11:29.929
THERE YOU GO,
YEAH.


1449
01:11:29.931 --> 01:11:32.064
HAPPY BOY...

1450
01:11:32.133 --> 01:11:33.633
NOT NOW, ADAM,
NOT NOW.


1451
01:11:36.003 --> 01:11:39.138
♪ THE WHEELS ON THE BUS
GO ROUND AND ROUND ♪


1452
01:11:39.207 --> 01:11:42.140
♪ ROUND AND ROUND
ROUND AND ROUND ♪


1453
01:11:42.177 --> 01:11:45.544
♪ THE WHEELS ON THE BUS
